34 /* fips wrapper calls, user can call direct */
35 #ifdef HAVE_FIPS
36  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* key, word32 len, const byte* iv,
37  int dir)
38  {
39  if (aes == NULL || !( (len == 16) || (len == 24) || (len == 32)) ) {
40  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
41  }
42 
43  return AesSetKey_fips(aes, key, len, iv, dir);
44  }
45  int wc_AesSetIV(Aes* aes, const byte* iv)
46  {
47  if (aes == NULL) {
48  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
49  }
50 
51  return AesSetIV_fips(aes, iv);
52  }
53  #ifdef HAVE_AES_CBC
54  int wc_AesCbcEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
55  {
56  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL) {
57  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
58  }
59 
60  return AesCbcEncrypt_fips(aes, out, in, sz);
61  }
62  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
63  int wc_AesCbcDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
64  {
65  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL
66  || sz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE != 0) {
67  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
68  }
69 
70  return AesCbcDecrypt_fips(aes, out, in, sz);
71  }
72  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
73  #endif /* HAVE_AES_CBC */

111  {
112  if (aes == NULL || !( (len == 16) || (len == 24) || (len == 32)) ) {

115

118  int wc_AesGcmEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz,
119  const byte* iv, word32 ivSz,
120  byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
121  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
122  {
123  if (aes == NULL || authTagSz > AES_BLOCK_SIZE
124  || authTagSz < WOLFSSL_MIN_AUTH_TAG_SZ ||
125  ivSz > AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
126  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
127  }
128 
129  return AesGcmEncrypt_fips(aes, out, in, sz, iv, ivSz, authTag,
130  authTagSz, authIn, authInSz);
131  }
132

142  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
143  }

146  authTagSz, authIn, authInSz);

150  int wc_GmacSetKey(Gmac* gmac, const byte* key, word32 len)
151  {
152  if (gmac == NULL || key == NULL || !((len == 16) ||
153  (len == 24) || (len == 32)) ) {
154  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
155  }
156 
157  return GmacSetKey(gmac, key, len);
158  }
159  int wc_GmacUpdate(Gmac* gmac, const byte* iv, word32 ivSz,
160  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz,
161  byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz)
162  {
163  if (gmac == NULL || authTagSz > AES_BLOCK_SIZE ||
164  authTagSz < WOLFSSL_MIN_AUTH_TAG_SZ) {
165  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
166  }
167 
168  return GmacUpdate(gmac, iv, ivSz, authIn, authInSz,
169  authTag, authTagSz);
170  }
171  #endif /* HAVE_AESGCM */

179  int wc_AesCcmEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
180  const byte* nonce, word32 nonceSz,
181  byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
182  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
183  {
184  /* sanity check on arguments */
185  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL || nonce == NULL
186  || authTag == NULL || nonceSz < 7 || nonceSz > 13)
187  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
188 
189  AesCcmEncrypt(aes, out, in, inSz, nonce, nonceSz, authTag,
190  authTagSz, authIn, authInSz);
191  return 0;
192  }
193 
194  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
195  int wc_AesCcmDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out,
196  const byte* in, word32 inSz,
197  const byte* nonce, word32 nonceSz,
198  const byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
199  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
200  {
201 
202  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL || nonce == NULL
203  || authTag == NULL || nonceSz < 7 || nonceSz > 13) {
204  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
205  }
206 
207  return AesCcmDecrypt(aes, out, in, inSz, nonce, nonceSz,
208  authTag, authTagSz, authIn, authInSz);

213  int wc_AesInit(Aes* aes, void* h, int i)
214  {
215  (void)aes;
216  (void)h;
217  (void)i;
218  /* FIPS doesn't support:
219  return AesInit(aes, h, i); */
220  return 0;
221  }
222  void wc_AesFree(Aes* aes)
223  {
224  (void)aes;
225  /* FIPS doesn't support:
226  AesFree(aes); */
227  }

257 /* Define AES implementation includes and functions */
258 #if defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
259  /* STM32F2/F4 hardware AES support for CBC, CTR modes */
260 
261  /* CRYPT_AES_GCM starts the IV with 2 */
262  #define STM32_GCM_IV_START 2
263 
264 #if defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT) || defined(HAVE_AESGCM) || defined(HAVE_AESCCM)
265  static int wc_AesEncrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
266  {
267  int ret = 0;
268  #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
269  CRYP_HandleTypeDef hcryp;
270 
271  XMEMSET(&hcryp, 0, sizeof(CRYP_HandleTypeDef));
272  switch(aes->rounds) {
273  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
274  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_128B;
275  break;
276  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
277  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;
278  break;
279  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
280  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_256B;
281  break;
282  default:
283  break;
284  }
285  hcryp.Instance = CRYP;
286  hcryp.Init.DataType = CRYP_DATATYPE_8B;
287  hcryp.Init.pKey = (uint8_t*)aes->key;
288 
289  HAL_CRYP_Init(&hcryp);
290 
291  if (HAL_CRYP_AESECB_Encrypt(&hcryp, (uint8_t*)inBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
292  outBlock, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT) != HAL_OK) {
293  ret = WC_TIMEOUT_E;
294  }
295 
296  HAL_CRYP_DeInit(&hcryp);
297  #else
298  word32 *enc_key;
299  CRYP_InitTypeDef AES_CRYP_InitStructure;
300  CRYP_KeyInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure;
301 
302  enc_key = aes->key;
303 
304  /* crypto structure initialization */
305  CRYP_KeyStructInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
306  CRYP_StructInit(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
307 
308  /* reset registers to their default values */
309  CRYP_DeInit();
310 
311  /* load key into correct registers */
312  switch (aes->rounds) {
313  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
314  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_128b;
315  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[0];
316  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[1];
317  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[2];
318  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[3];
319  break;
320 
321  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
322  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_192b;
323  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[0];
324  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[1];
325  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[2];
326  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[3];
327  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[4];
328  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[5];
329  break;
330 
331  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
332  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_256b;
333  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Left = enc_key[0];
334  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Right = enc_key[1];
335  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[2];
336  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[3];
337  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[4];
338  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[5];
339  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[6];
340  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[7];
341  break;
342 
343  default:
344  break;
345  }
346  CRYP_KeyInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
347 
348  /* set direction, mode, and datatype */
349  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoDir = CRYP_AlgoDir_Encrypt;
350  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoMode = CRYP_AlgoMode_AES_ECB;
351  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_DataType = CRYP_DataType_8b;
352  CRYP_Init(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
353 
354  /* enable crypto processor */
355  CRYP_Cmd(ENABLE);
356 
357  /* flush IN/OUT FIFOs */
358  CRYP_FIFOFlush();
359 
360  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[0]);
361  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[4]);
362  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[8]);
363  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[12]);
364 
365  /* wait until the complete message has been processed */
366  while (CRYP_GetFlagStatus(CRYP_FLAG_BUSY) != RESET) {}
367 
368  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[0] = CRYP_DataOut();
369  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[4] = CRYP_DataOut();
370  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[8] = CRYP_DataOut();
371  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[12] = CRYP_DataOut();
372 
373  /* disable crypto processor */
374  CRYP_Cmd(DISABLE);
375  #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
376  return ret;
377  }
378 #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT || HAVE_AESGCM || HAVE_AESCCM */
379 
380 #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
381  #if defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT) || defined(HAVE_AESCCM)
382  static int wc_AesDecrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
383  {
384  int ret = 0;
385  #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
386  CRYP_HandleTypeDef hcryp;
387 
388  XMEMSET(&hcryp, 0, sizeof(CRYP_HandleTypeDef));
389  switch(aes->rounds) {
390  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
391  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_128B;
392  break;
393  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
394  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;
395  break;
396  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
397  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_256B;
398  break;
399  default:
400  break;
401  }
402  hcryp.Instance = CRYP;
403  hcryp.Init.DataType = CRYP_DATATYPE_8B;
404  hcryp.Init.pKey = (uint8_t*)aes->key;
405 
406  HAL_CRYP_Init(&hcryp);
407 
408  if (HAL_CRYP_AESECB_Decrypt(&hcryp, (uint8_t*)inBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
409  outBlock, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT) != HAL_OK) {
410  ret = WC_TIMEOUT_E;
411  }
412 
413  HAL_CRYP_DeInit(&hcryp);
414  #else
415  word32 *enc_key;
416  CRYP_InitTypeDef AES_CRYP_InitStructure;
417  CRYP_KeyInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure;
418 
419  enc_key = aes->key;
420 
421  /* crypto structure initialization */
422  CRYP_KeyStructInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
423  CRYP_StructInit(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
424 
425  /* reset registers to their default values */
426  CRYP_DeInit();
427 
428  /* load key into correct registers */
429  switch (aes->rounds) {
430  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
431  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_128b;
432  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[0];
433  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[1];
434  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[2];
435  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[3];
436  break;
437 
438  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
439  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_192b;
440  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[0];
441  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[1];
442  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[2];
443  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[3];
444  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[4];
445  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[5];
446  break;
447 
448  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
449  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_256b;
450  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Left = enc_key[0];
451  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Right = enc_key[1];
452  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[2];
453  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[3];
454  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[4];
455  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[5];
456  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[6];
457  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[7];
458  break;
459 
460  default:
461  break;
462  }
463  CRYP_KeyInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
464 
465  /* set direction, mode, and datatype */
466  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoDir = CRYP_AlgoDir_Decrypt;
467  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoMode = CRYP_AlgoMode_AES_ECB;
468  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_DataType = CRYP_DataType_8b;
469  CRYP_Init(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
470 
471  /* enable crypto processor */
472  CRYP_Cmd(ENABLE);
473 
474  /* flush IN/OUT FIFOs */
475  CRYP_FIFOFlush();
476 
477  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[0]);
478  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[4]);
479  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[8]);
480  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&inBlock[12]);
481 
482  /* wait until the complete message has been processed */
483  while (CRYP_GetFlagStatus(CRYP_FLAG_BUSY) != RESET) {}
484 
485  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[0] = CRYP_DataOut();
486  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[4] = CRYP_DataOut();
487  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[8] = CRYP_DataOut();
488  *(uint32_t*)&outBlock[12] = CRYP_DataOut();
489 
490  /* disable crypto processor */
491  CRYP_Cmd(DISABLE);
492  #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
493  return ret;
494  }
495  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT || HAVE_AESCCM */
496 #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
497 
498 #elif defined(HAVE_COLDFIRE_SEC)
499  /* Freescale Coldfire SEC support for CBC mode.
500  * NOTE: no support for AES-CTR/GCM/CCM/Direct */
501  #include <wolfssl/wolfcrypt/types.h>
502  #include "sec.h"
503  #include "mcf5475_sec.h"
504  #include "mcf5475_siu.h"
505 #elif defined(FREESCALE_LTC)
506  #include "fsl_ltc.h"
507  #if defined(FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM)
508  #undef NEED_AES_TABLES
509  #undef GCM_TABLE
510  #else
511  /* if LTC doesn't have GCM, use software with LTC AES ECB mode */
512  static int wc_AesEncrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
513  {
514  wc_AesEncryptDirect(aes, outBlock, inBlock);
515  return 0;

517  static int wc_AesDecrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
518  {
519  wc_AesDecryptDirect(aes, outBlock, inBlock);
520  return 0;
521  }
522  #endif
523 #elif defined(FREESCALE_MMCAU)
524  /* Freescale mmCAU hardware AES support for Direct, CBC, CCM, GCM modes
525  * through the CAU/mmCAU library. Documentation located in
526  * ColdFire/ColdFire+ CAU and Kinetis mmCAU Software Library User
527  * Guide (See note in README). */
528  #ifdef FREESCALE_MMCAU_CLASSIC
529  /* MMCAU 1.4 library used with non-KSDK / classic MQX builds */
530  #include "cau_api.h"
531  #else
532  #include "fsl_mmcau.h"
533  #endif
534 
535  static int wc_AesEncrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
536  {
537  int ret;
538 
539  #ifdef FREESCALE_MMCAU_CLASSIC
540  if ((wolfssl_word)outBlock % WOLFSSL_MMCAU_ALIGNMENT) {
541  WOLFSSL_MSG("Bad cau_aes_encrypt alignment");
542  return BAD_ALIGN_E;
543  }
544  #endif
545 
546  ret = wolfSSL_CryptHwMutexLock();
547  if(ret == 0) {
548  #ifdef FREESCALE_MMCAU_CLASSIC
549  cau_aes_encrypt(inBlock, (byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds, outBlock);
550  #else
551  MMCAU_AES_EncryptEcb(inBlock, (byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds,
552  outBlock);
553  #endif
554  wolfSSL_CryptHwMutexUnLock();
555  }
556  return ret;
557  }
558  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
559  static int wc_AesDecrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
560  {
561  int ret;
562 
563  #ifdef FREESCALE_MMCAU_CLASSIC
564  if ((wolfssl_word)outBlock % WOLFSSL_MMCAU_ALIGNMENT) {
565  WOLFSSL_MSG("Bad cau_aes_decrypt alignment");
566  return BAD_ALIGN_E;
567  }
568  #endif
569 
570  ret = wolfSSL_CryptHwMutexLock();
571  if(ret == 0) {
572  #ifdef FREESCALE_MMCAU_CLASSIC
573  cau_aes_decrypt(inBlock, (byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds, outBlock);
574  #else
575  MMCAU_AES_DecryptEcb(inBlock, (byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds,
576  outBlock);
577  #endif
578  wolfSSL_CryptHwMutexUnLock();
579  }
580  return ret;
581  }
582  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
583 
584 #elif defined(WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT)
585 
586  #include <wolfssl/wolfcrypt/port/pic32/pic32mz-crypt.h>
587 
588  #if defined(HAVE_AESGCM) || defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT)
589 
590  static int wc_AesEncrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
591  {
592  return wc_Pic32AesCrypt(aes->key_ce, aes->keylen, NULL, 0,
593  outBlock, inBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
594  PIC32_ENCRYPTION, PIC32_ALGO_AES, PIC32_CRYPTOALGO_RECB);
595  }

689  void AES_128_Key_Expansion(const unsigned char* userkey,
690  unsigned char* key_schedule)
691  XASM_LINK("AES_128_Key_Expansion");
692 
693  void AES_192_Key_Expansion(const unsigned char* userkey,
694  unsigned char* key_schedule)
695  XASM_LINK("AES_192_Key_Expansion");
696 
697  void AES_256_Key_Expansion(const unsigned char* userkey,
698  unsigned char* key_schedule)
699  XASM_LINK("AES_256_Key_Expansion");
700 
701 
702  static int AES_set_encrypt_key(const unsigned char *userKey, const int bits,
703  Aes* aes)
704  {
705  int ret;
706 
707  if (!userKey || !aes)
708  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
709 
710  switch (bits) {
711  case 128:
712  AES_128_Key_Expansion (userKey,(byte*)aes->key); aes->rounds = 10;
713  return 0;
714  case 192:
715  AES_192_Key_Expansion (userKey,(byte*)aes->key); aes->rounds = 12;
716  return 0;
717  case 256:
718  AES_256_Key_Expansion (userKey,(byte*)aes->key); aes->rounds = 14;
719  return 0;
720  default:
721  ret = BAD_FUNC_ARG;
722  }
723 
724  return ret;
725  }
726 
727  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
728  static int AES_set_decrypt_key(const unsigned char* userKey,
729  const int bits, Aes* aes)
730  {
731  int nr;
732  Aes temp_key;
733  __m128i *Key_Schedule = (__m128i*)aes->key;
734  __m128i *Temp_Key_Schedule = (__m128i*)temp_key.key;
735 
736  if (!userKey || !aes)
737  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
738 
739  if (AES_set_encrypt_key(userKey,bits,&temp_key) == BAD_FUNC_ARG)
740  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
741 
742  nr = temp_key.rounds;
743  aes->rounds = nr;
744 
745  Key_Schedule[nr] = Temp_Key_Schedule[0];
746  Key_Schedule[nr-1] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[1]);
747  Key_Schedule[nr-2] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[2]);
748  Key_Schedule[nr-3] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[3]);
749  Key_Schedule[nr-4] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[4]);
750  Key_Schedule[nr-5] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[5]);
751  Key_Schedule[nr-6] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[6]);
752  Key_Schedule[nr-7] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[7]);
753  Key_Schedule[nr-8] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[8]);
754  Key_Schedule[nr-9] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[9]);
755 
756  if (nr>10) {
757  Key_Schedule[nr-10] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[10]);
758  Key_Schedule[nr-11] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[11]);
759  }
760 
761  if (nr>12) {
762  Key_Schedule[nr-12] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[12]);
763  Key_Schedule[nr-13] = _mm_aesimc_si128(Temp_Key_Schedule[13]);
764  }
765 
766  Key_Schedule[0] = Temp_Key_Schedule[nr];
767 
768  return 0;
769  }
770  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
771

1356  0x47U, 0xf1U, 0x1aU, 0x71U, 0x1dU, 0x29U, 0xc5U, 0x89U,
1357  0x6fU, 0xb7U, 0x62U, 0x0eU, 0xaaU, 0x18U, 0xbeU, 0x1bU,
1358  0xfcU, 0x56U, 0x3eU, 0x4bU, 0xc6U, 0xd2U, 0x79U, 0x20U,
1359  0x9aU, 0xdbU, 0xc0U, 0xfeU, 0x78U, 0xcdU, 0x5aU, 0xf4U,
1360  0x1fU, 0xddU, 0xa8U, 0x33U, 0x88U, 0x07U, 0xc7U, 0x31U,
1361  0xb1U, 0x12U, 0x10U, 0x59U, 0x27U, 0x80U, 0xecU, 0x5fU,
1362  0x60U, 0x51U, 0x7fU, 0xa9U, 0x19U, 0xb5U, 0x4aU, 0x0dU,
1363  0x2dU, 0xe5U, 0x7aU, 0x9fU, 0x93U, 0xc9U, 0x9cU, 0xefU,
1364  0xa0U, 0xe0U, 0x3bU, 0x4dU, 0xaeU, 0x2aU, 0xf5U, 0xb0U,
1365  0xc8U, 0xebU, 0xbbU, 0x3cU, 0x83U, 0x53U, 0x99U, 0x61U,
1366  0x17U, 0x2bU, 0x04U, 0x7eU, 0xbaU, 0x77U, 0xd6U, 0x26U,
1367  0xe1U, 0x69U, 0x14U, 0x63U, 0x55U, 0x21U, 0x0cU, 0x7dU,
1368 };
1369 #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
1370 
1371 #define GETBYTE(x, y) (word32)((byte)((x) >> (8 * (y))))
1372 
1373 
1374 
1375 #if defined(HAVE_AES_CBC) || defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT) || defined(HAVE_AESGCM)
1376 
1377 #ifndef WC_CACHE_LINE_SZ
1378  #if defined(__x86_64__) || defined(_M_X64) || \
1379  (defined(__ILP32__) && (__ILP32__ >= 1))
1380  #define WC_CACHE_LINE_SZ 64
1381  #else
1382  /* default cache line size */
1383  #define WC_CACHE_LINE_SZ 32
1384  #endif
1385 #endif
1386 
1387 
1388 /* load 4 Te Tables into cache by cache line stride */
1389 static INLINE word32 PreFetchTe(void)
1390 {
1391  word32 x = 0;
1392  int i,j;
1393 
1394  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1395  /* 256 elements, each one is 4 bytes */
1396  for (j = 0; j < 256; j += WC_CACHE_LINE_SZ/4) {
1397  x &= Te[i][j];
1398  }
1399  }
1400  return x;
1401 }
1402 
1403 
1404 static void wc_AesEncrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
1405 {
1406  word32 s0, s1, s2, s3;
1407  word32 t0, t1, t2, t3;
1408  word32 r = aes->rounds >> 1;
1409  const word32* rk = aes->key;
1410 
1411  if (r > 7 || r == 0) {
1412  WOLFSSL_MSG("AesEncrypt encountered improper key, set it up");
1413  return; /* stop instead of segfaulting, set up your keys! */
1414  }
1415 
1416 #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
1417  if (haveAESNI && aes->use_aesni) {
1418  #ifdef DEBUG_AESNI
1419  printf("about to aes encrypt\n");
1420  printf("in = %p\n", inBlock);
1421  printf("out = %p\n", outBlock);
1422  printf("aes->key = %p\n", aes->key);
1423  printf("aes->rounds = %d\n", aes->rounds);
1424  printf("sz = %d\n", AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
1425  #endif
1426 
1427  /* check alignment, decrypt doesn't need alignment */
1428  if ((wolfssl_word)inBlock % AESNI_ALIGN) {
1429  #ifndef NO_WOLFSSL_ALLOC_ALIGN
1430  byte* tmp = (byte*)XMALLOC(AES_BLOCK_SIZE + AESNI_ALIGN, aes->heap,
1431  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
1432  byte* tmp_align;
1433  if (tmp == NULL) return;
1434 
1435  tmp_align = tmp + (AESNI_ALIGN - ((size_t)tmp % AESNI_ALIGN));
1436 
1437  XMEMCPY(tmp_align, inBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
1438  AES_ECB_encrypt(tmp_align, tmp_align, AES_BLOCK_SIZE, (byte*)aes->key,
1439  aes->rounds);
1440  XMEMCPY(outBlock, tmp_align, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
1441  XFREE(tmp, aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
1442  return;
1443  #else
1444  WOLFSSL_MSG("AES-ECB encrypt with bad alignment");
1445  return;
1446  #endif
1447  }
1448 
1449  AES_ECB_encrypt(inBlock, outBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE, (byte*)aes->key,
1450  aes->rounds);
1451 
1452  return;
1453  }
1454  else {
1455  #ifdef DEBUG_AESNI
1456  printf("Skipping AES-NI\n");
1457  #endif
1458  }
1459 #endif
1460 
1461  /*
1462  * map byte array block to cipher state
1463  * and add initial round key:
1464  */
1465  XMEMCPY(&s0, inBlock, sizeof(s0));
1466  XMEMCPY(&s1, inBlock + sizeof(s0), sizeof(s1));
1467  XMEMCPY(&s2, inBlock + 2 * sizeof(s0), sizeof(s2));
1468  XMEMCPY(&s3, inBlock + 3 * sizeof(s0), sizeof(s3));
1469 
1470 #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
1471  s0 = ByteReverseWord32(s0);
1472  s1 = ByteReverseWord32(s1);
1473  s2 = ByteReverseWord32(s2);
1474  s3 = ByteReverseWord32(s3);
1475 #endif
1476 
1477  s0 ^= rk[0];
1478  s1 ^= rk[1];
1479  s2 ^= rk[2];
1480  s3 ^= rk[3];
1481 
1482  s0 |= PreFetchTe();
1483 
1484  /*
1485  * Nr - 1 full rounds:
1486  */
1487 
1488  for (;;) {
1489  t0 =
1490  Te[0][GETBYTE(s0, 3)] ^
1491  Te[1][GETBYTE(s1, 2)] ^
1492  Te[2][GETBYTE(s2, 1)] ^
1493  Te[3][GETBYTE(s3, 0)] ^
1494  rk[4];
1495  t1 =
1496  Te[0][GETBYTE(s1, 3)] ^
1497  Te[1][GETBYTE(s2, 2)] ^
1498  Te[2][GETBYTE(s3, 1)] ^
1499  Te[3][GETBYTE(s0, 0)] ^
1500  rk[5];
1501  t2 =
1502  Te[0][GETBYTE(s2, 3)] ^
1503  Te[1][GETBYTE(s3, 2)] ^
1504  Te[2][GETBYTE(s0, 1)] ^
1505  Te[3][GETBYTE(s1, 0)] ^
1506  rk[6];
1507  t3 =
1508  Te[0][GETBYTE(s3, 3)] ^
1509  Te[1][GETBYTE(s0, 2)] ^
1510  Te[2][GETBYTE(s1, 1)] ^
1511  Te[3][GETBYTE(s2, 0)] ^
1512  rk[7];
1513 
1514  rk += 8;
1515  if (--r == 0) {
1516  break;
1517  }
1518 
1519  s0 =
1520  Te[0][GETBYTE(t0, 3)] ^
1521  Te[1][GETBYTE(t1, 2)] ^
1522  Te[2][GETBYTE(t2, 1)] ^
1523  Te[3][GETBYTE(t3, 0)] ^
1524  rk[0];
1525  s1 =
1526  Te[0][GETBYTE(t1, 3)] ^
1527  Te[1][GETBYTE(t2, 2)] ^
1528  Te[2][GETBYTE(t3, 1)] ^
1529  Te[3][GETBYTE(t0, 0)] ^
1530  rk[1];
1531  s2 =
1532  Te[0][GETBYTE(t2, 3)] ^
1533  Te[1][GETBYTE(t3, 2)] ^
1534  Te[2][GETBYTE(t0, 1)] ^
1535  Te[3][GETBYTE(t1, 0)] ^
1536  rk[2];
1537  s3 =
1538  Te[0][GETBYTE(t3, 3)] ^
1539  Te[1][GETBYTE(t0, 2)] ^
1540  Te[2][GETBYTE(t1, 1)] ^
1541  Te[3][GETBYTE(t2, 0)] ^
1542  rk[3];
1543  }
1544 
1545  /*
1546  * apply last round and
1547  * map cipher state to byte array block:
1548  */
1549 
1550  s0 =
1551  (Te[2][GETBYTE(t0, 3)] & 0xff000000) ^
1552  (Te[3][GETBYTE(t1, 2)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
1553  (Te[0][GETBYTE(t2, 1)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
1554  (Te[1][GETBYTE(t3, 0)] & 0x000000ff) ^
1555  rk[0];
1556  s1 =
1557  (Te[2][GETBYTE(t1, 3)] & 0xff000000) ^
1558  (Te[3][GETBYTE(t2, 2)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
1559  (Te[0][GETBYTE(t3, 1)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
1560  (Te[1][GETBYTE(t0, 0)] & 0x000000ff) ^
1561  rk[1];
1562  s2 =
1563  (Te[2][GETBYTE(t2, 3)] & 0xff000000) ^
1564  (Te[3][GETBYTE(t3, 2)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
1565  (Te[0][GETBYTE(t0, 1)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
1566  (Te[1][GETBYTE(t1, 0)] & 0x000000ff) ^
1567  rk[2];
1568  s3 =
1569  (Te[2][GETBYTE(t3, 3)] & 0xff000000) ^
1570  (Te[3][GETBYTE(t0, 2)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
1571  (Te[0][GETBYTE(t1, 1)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
1572  (Te[1][GETBYTE(t2, 0)] & 0x000000ff) ^
1573  rk[3];
1574 
1575  /* write out */
1576 #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
1577  s0 = ByteReverseWord32(s0);
1578  s1 = ByteReverseWord32(s1);
1579  s2 = ByteReverseWord32(s2);
1580  s3 = ByteReverseWord32(s3);
1581 #endif
1582 
1583  XMEMCPY(outBlock, &s0, sizeof(s0));
1584  XMEMCPY(outBlock + sizeof(s0), &s1, sizeof(s1));
1585  XMEMCPY(outBlock + 2 * sizeof(s0), &s2, sizeof(s2));
1586  XMEMCPY(outBlock + 3 * sizeof(s0), &s3, sizeof(s3));
1587 
1588 }
1589 #endif /* HAVE_AES_CBC || WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT || HAVE_AESGCM */
1590 
1591 #if defined(HAVE_AES_DECRYPT)
1592 #if defined(HAVE_AES_CBC) || defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT)
1593 
1594 /* load 4 Td Tables into cache by cache line stride */
1595 static INLINE word32 PreFetchTd(void)
1596 {
1597  word32 x = 0;
1598  int i,j;
1599 
1600  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1601  /* 256 elements, each one is 4 bytes */
1602  for (j = 0; j < 256; j += WC_CACHE_LINE_SZ/4) {
1603  x &= Td[i][j];
1604  }
1605  }
1606  return x;
1607 }
1608 
1609 /* load Td Table4 into cache by cache line stride */
1610 static INLINE word32 PreFetchTd4(void)
1611 {
1612  word32 x = 0;
1613  int i;
1614 
1615  for (i = 0; i < 256; i += WC_CACHE_LINE_SZ) {
1616  x &= (word32)Td4[i];
1617  }
1618  return x;
1619 }
1620 
1621 static void wc_AesDecrypt(Aes* aes, const byte* inBlock, byte* outBlock)
1622 {
1623  word32 s0, s1, s2, s3;
1624  word32 t0, t1, t2, t3;
1625  word32 r = aes->rounds >> 1;
1626 
1627  const word32* rk = aes->key;
1628  if (r > 7 || r == 0) {
1629  WOLFSSL_MSG("AesDecrypt encountered improper key, set it up");
1630  return; /* stop instead of segfaulting, set up your keys! */
1631  }
1632 #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
1633  if (haveAESNI && aes->use_aesni) {
1634  #ifdef DEBUG_AESNI
1635  printf("about to aes decrypt\n");
1636  printf("in = %p\n", inBlock);
1637  printf("out = %p\n", outBlock);
1638  printf("aes->key = %p\n", aes->key);
1639  printf("aes->rounds = %d\n", aes->rounds);
1640  printf("sz = %d\n", AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
1641  #endif
1642 
1643  /* if input and output same will overwrite input iv */
1644  XMEMCPY(aes->tmp, inBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
1645  AES_ECB_decrypt(inBlock, outBlock, AES_BLOCK_SIZE, (byte*)aes->key,
1646  aes->rounds);
1647  return;
1648  }
1649  else {
1650  #ifdef DEBUG_AESNI
1651  printf("Skipping AES-NI\n");
1652  #endif
1653  }
1654 #endif /* WOLFSSL_AESNI */
1655 
1656  /*
1657  * map byte array block to cipher state
1658  * and add initial round key:
1659  */
1660  XMEMCPY(&s0, inBlock, sizeof(s0));
1661  XMEMCPY(&s1, inBlock + sizeof(s0), sizeof(s1));
1662  XMEMCPY(&s2, inBlock + 2 * sizeof(s0), sizeof(s2));
1663  XMEMCPY(&s3, inBlock + 3 * sizeof(s0), sizeof(s3));
1664 
1665 #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
1666  s0 = ByteReverseWord32(s0);
1667  s1 = ByteReverseWord32(s1);
1668  s2 = ByteReverseWord32(s2);
1669  s3 = ByteReverseWord32(s3);
1670 #endif
1671 
1672  s0 ^= rk[0];
1673  s1 ^= rk[1];
1674  s2 ^= rk[2];
1675  s3 ^= rk[3];
1676 
1677  s0 |= PreFetchTd();
1678 
1679  /*
1680  * Nr - 1 full rounds:
1681  */
1682 
1683  for (;;) {
1684  t0 =
1685  Td[0][GETBYTE(s0, 3)] ^
1686  Td[1][GETBYTE(s3, 2)] ^
1687  Td[2][GETBYTE(s2, 1)] ^
1688  Td[3][GETBYTE(s1, 0)] ^
1689  rk[4];
1690  t1 =
1691  Td[0][GETBYTE(s1, 3)] ^
1692  Td[1][GETBYTE(s0, 2)] ^
1693  Td[2][GETBYTE(s3, 1)] ^
1694  Td[3][GETBYTE(s2, 0)] ^
1695  rk[5];
1696  t2 =
1697  Td[0][GETBYTE(s2, 3)] ^
1698  Td[1][GETBYTE(s1, 2)] ^
1699  Td[2][GETBYTE(s0, 1)] ^
1700  Td[3][GETBYTE(s3, 0)] ^
1701  rk[6];
1702  t3 =
1703  Td[0][GETBYTE(s3, 3)] ^
1704  Td[1][GETBYTE(s2, 2)] ^
1705  Td[2][GETBYTE(s1, 1)] ^
1706  Td[3][GETBYTE(s0, 0)] ^
1707  rk[7];
1708 
1709  rk += 8;
1710  if (--r == 0) {
1711  break;
1712  }
1713 
1714  s0 =
1715  Td[0][GETBYTE(t0, 3)] ^
1716  Td[1][GETBYTE(t3, 2)] ^
1717  Td[2][GETBYTE(t2, 1)] ^
1718  Td[3][GETBYTE(t1, 0)] ^
1719  rk[0];
1720  s1 =
1721  Td[0][GETBYTE(t1, 3)] ^
1722  Td[1][GETBYTE(t0, 2)] ^
1723  Td[2][GETBYTE(t3, 1)] ^
1724  Td[3][GETBYTE(t2, 0)] ^
1725  rk[1];
1726  s2 =
1727  Td[0][GETBYTE(t2, 3)] ^
1728  Td[1][GETBYTE(t1, 2)] ^
1729  Td[2][GETBYTE(t0, 1)] ^
1730  Td[3][GETBYTE(t3, 0)] ^
1731  rk[2];
1732  s3 =
1733  Td[0][GETBYTE(t3, 3)] ^
1734  Td[1][GETBYTE(t2, 2)] ^
1735  Td[2][GETBYTE(t1, 1)] ^
1736  Td[3][GETBYTE(t0, 0)] ^
1737  rk[3];
1738  }
1739  /*
1740  * apply last round and
1741  * map cipher state to byte array block:
1742  */
1743 
1744  t0 |= PreFetchTd4();
1745 
1746  s0 =
1747  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t0, 3)] << 24) ^
1748  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t3, 2)] << 16) ^
1749  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t2, 1)] << 8) ^
1750  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t1, 0)]) ^
1751  rk[0];
1752  s1 =
1753  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t1, 3)] << 24) ^
1754  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t0, 2)] << 16) ^
1755  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t3, 1)] << 8) ^
1756  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t2, 0)]) ^
1757  rk[1];
1758  s2 =
1759  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t2, 3)] << 24) ^
1760  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t1, 2)] << 16) ^
1761  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t0, 1)] << 8) ^
1762  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t3, 0)]) ^
1763  rk[2];
1764  s3 =
1765  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t3, 3)] << 24) ^
1766  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t2, 2)] << 16) ^
1767  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t1, 1)] << 8) ^
1768  ((word32)Td4[GETBYTE(t0, 0)]) ^
1769  rk[3];
1770 
1771  /* write out */
1772 #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
1773  s0 = ByteReverseWord32(s0);
1774  s1 = ByteReverseWord32(s1);
1775  s2 = ByteReverseWord32(s2);
1776  s3 = ByteReverseWord32(s3);
1777 #endif
1778 
1779  XMEMCPY(outBlock, &s0, sizeof(s0));
1780  XMEMCPY(outBlock + sizeof(s0), &s1, sizeof(s1));
1781  XMEMCPY(outBlock + 2 * sizeof(s0), &s2, sizeof(s2));
1782  XMEMCPY(outBlock + 3 * sizeof(s0), &s3, sizeof(s3));
1783 }
1784 #endif /* HAVE_AES_CBC || WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT */
1785 #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
1786 
1787 #endif /* NEED_AES_TABLES */

1791 /* wc_AesSetKey */
1792 #if defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
1793 
1794  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1795  const byte* iv, int dir)
1796  {
1797  word32 *rk = aes->key;
1798 
1799  (void)dir;
1800 
1801  if (!((keylen == 16) || (keylen == 24) || (keylen == 32)))
1802  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1803 
1804  aes->keylen = keylen;
1805  aes->rounds = keylen/4 + 6;
1806  XMEMCPY(rk, userKey, keylen);
1807  #ifndef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
1808  ByteReverseWords(rk, rk, keylen);
1809  #endif
1810 
1811  return wc_AesSetIV(aes, iv);
1812  }
1813  #if defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT)
1814  int wc_AesSetKeyDirect(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1815  const byte* iv, int dir)
1816  {
1817  return wc_AesSetKey(aes, userKey, keylen, iv, dir);
1818  }
1819  #endif
1820 
1821 #elif defined(HAVE_COLDFIRE_SEC)
1822  #if defined (HAVE_THREADX)
1823  #include "memory_pools.h"
1824  extern TX_BYTE_POOL mp_ncached; /* Non Cached memory pool */
1825  #endif
1826 
1827  #define AES_BUFFER_SIZE (AES_BLOCK_SIZE * 64)
1828  static unsigned char *AESBuffIn = NULL;
1829  static unsigned char *AESBuffOut = NULL;
1830  static byte *secReg;
1831  static byte *secKey;
1832  static volatile SECdescriptorType *secDesc;
1833 
1834  static wolfSSL_Mutex Mutex_AesSEC;
1835 
1836  #define SEC_DESC_AES_CBC_ENCRYPT 0x60300010
1837  #define SEC_DESC_AES_CBC_DECRYPT 0x60200010
1838 
1839  extern volatile unsigned char __MBAR[];
1840 
1841  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1842  const byte* iv, int dir)
1843  {
1844  if (AESBuffIn == NULL) {
1845  #if defined (HAVE_THREADX)
1846  int s1, s2, s3, s4, s5;
1847  s5 = tx_byte_allocate(&mp_ncached,(void *)&secDesc,
1848  sizeof(SECdescriptorType), TX_NO_WAIT);
1849  s1 = tx_byte_allocate(&mp_ncached, (void *)&AESBuffIn,
1850  AES_BUFFER_SIZE, TX_NO_WAIT);
1851  s2 = tx_byte_allocate(&mp_ncached, (void *)&AESBuffOut,
1852  AES_BUFFER_SIZE, TX_NO_WAIT);
1853  s3 = tx_byte_allocate(&mp_ncached, (void *)&secKey,
1854  AES_BLOCK_SIZE*2, TX_NO_WAIT);
1855  s4 = tx_byte_allocate(&mp_ncached, (void *)&secReg,
1856  AES_BLOCK_SIZE, TX_NO_WAIT);
1857 
1858  if (s1 || s2 || s3 || s4 || s5)
1859  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1860  #else
1861  #warning "Allocate non-Cache buffers"
1862  #endif
1863 
1864  wc_InitMutex(&Mutex_AesSEC);
1865  }
1866 
1867  if (!((keylen == 16) || (keylen == 24) || (keylen == 32)))
1868  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1869 
1870  if (aes == NULL)
1871  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1872 
1873  aes->keylen = keylen;
1874  aes->rounds = keylen/4 + 6;
1875  XMEMCPY(aes->key, userKey, keylen);
1876 
1877  if (iv)
1878  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
1879 
1880  return 0;
1881  }
1882 #elif defined(FREESCALE_LTC)
1883  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen, const byte* iv,
1884  int dir)
1885  {
1886  if (!((keylen == 16) || (keylen == 24) || (keylen == 32)))
1887  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1888 
1889  aes->rounds = keylen/4 + 6;
1890  XMEMCPY(aes->key, userKey, keylen);
1891 
1892  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER
1893  aes->left = 0;
1894  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER */
1895 
1896  return wc_AesSetIV(aes, iv);
1897  }
1898 
1899  int wc_AesSetKeyDirect(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1900  const byte* iv, int dir)
1901  {
1902  return wc_AesSetKey(aes, userKey, keylen, iv, dir);
1903  }
1904 #elif defined(FREESCALE_MMCAU)
1905  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1906  const byte* iv, int dir)
1907  {
1908  int ret;
1909  byte *rk = (byte*)aes->key;
1910 
1911  (void)dir;
1912 
1913  if (!((keylen == 16) || (keylen == 24) || (keylen == 32)))
1914  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1915 
1916  if (rk == NULL)
1917  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1918 
1919  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER
1920  aes->left = 0;
1921  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER */
1922 
1923  aes->keylen = keylen;
1924  aes->rounds = keylen/4 + 6;
1925 
1926  ret = wolfSSL_CryptHwMutexLock();
1927  if(ret == 0) {
1928  #ifdef FREESCALE_MMCAU_CLASSIC
1929  cau_aes_set_key(userKey, keylen*8, rk);
1930  #else
1931  MMCAU_AES_SetKey(userKey, keylen, rk);
1932  #endif
1933  wolfSSL_CryptHwMutexUnLock();
1934 
1935  ret = wc_AesSetIV(aes, iv);
1936  }
1937 
1938  return ret;
1939  }
1940 
1941  int wc_AesSetKeyDirect(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1942  const byte* iv, int dir)
1943  {
1944  return wc_AesSetKey(aes, userKey, keylen, iv, dir);
1945  }
1946 
1947 #elif defined(WOLFSSL_NRF51_AES)
1948  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1949  const byte* iv, int dir)
1950  {
1951  int ret;
1952 
1953  (void)dir;
1954  (void)iv;
1955 
1956  if (keylen != 16)
1957  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1958 
1959  aes->keylen = keylen;
1960  aes->rounds = keylen/4 + 6;
1961  ret = nrf51_aes_set_key(userKey);
1962 
1963  return ret;
1964  }
1965 
1966  int wc_AesSetKeyDirect(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1967  const byte* iv, int dir)
1968  {
1969  return wc_AesSetKey(aes, userKey, keylen, iv, dir);
1970  }
1971 
1972 #else
1973  static int wc_AesSetKeyLocal(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
1974  const byte* iv, int dir)
1975  {
1976  word32 *rk = aes->key;
1977  #ifdef NEED_AES_TABLES
1978  word32 temp;
1979  unsigned int i = 0;
1980  #endif
1981 
1982  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
1983  aes->use_aesni = 0;
1984  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AESNI */
1985  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER
1986  aes->left = 0;
1987  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER */
1988 
1989  aes->keylen = keylen;
1990  aes->rounds = (keylen/4) + 6;
1991 
1992  XMEMCPY(rk, userKey, keylen);
1993  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
1994  ByteReverseWords(rk, rk, keylen);
1995  #endif
1996 
1997  #ifdef WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT
1998  XMEMCPY((word32*)aes->key_ce, userKey, keylen);
1999  #endif
2000 
2001 #ifdef NEED_AES_TABLES
2002 
2003  switch (keylen) {
2004  #if defined(AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE) && AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE >= 128
2005  case 16:
2006  while (1)
2007  {
2008  temp = rk[3];
2009  rk[4] = rk[0] ^
2010  (Te[2][GETBYTE(temp, 2)] & 0xff000000) ^
2011  (Te[3][GETBYTE(temp, 1)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
2012  (Te[0][GETBYTE(temp, 0)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
2013  (Te[1][GETBYTE(temp, 3)] & 0x000000ff) ^
2014  rcon[i];
2015  rk[5] = rk[1] ^ rk[4];
2016  rk[6] = rk[2] ^ rk[5];
2017  rk[7] = rk[3] ^ rk[6];
2018  if (++i == 10)
2019  break;
2020  rk += 4;
2021  }
2022  break;
2023  #endif /* 128 */
2024 
2025  #if defined(AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE) && AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE >= 192
2026  case 24:
2027  /* for (;;) here triggers a bug in VC60 SP4 w/ Pro Pack */
2028  while (1)
2029  {
2030  temp = rk[ 5];
2031  rk[ 6] = rk[ 0] ^
2032  (Te[2][GETBYTE(temp, 2)] & 0xff000000) ^
2033  (Te[3][GETBYTE(temp, 1)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
2034  (Te[0][GETBYTE(temp, 0)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
2035  (Te[1][GETBYTE(temp, 3)] & 0x000000ff) ^
2036  rcon[i];
2037  rk[ 7] = rk[ 1] ^ rk[ 6];
2038  rk[ 8] = rk[ 2] ^ rk[ 7];
2039  rk[ 9] = rk[ 3] ^ rk[ 8];
2040  if (++i == 8)
2041  break;
2042  rk[10] = rk[ 4] ^ rk[ 9];
2043  rk[11] = rk[ 5] ^ rk[10];
2044  rk += 6;
2045  }
2046  break;
2047  #endif /* 192 */
2048 
2049  #if defined(AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE) && AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE >= 256
2050  case 32:
2051  while (1)
2052  {
2053  temp = rk[ 7];
2054  rk[ 8] = rk[ 0] ^
2055  (Te[2][GETBYTE(temp, 2)] & 0xff000000) ^
2056  (Te[3][GETBYTE(temp, 1)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
2057  (Te[0][GETBYTE(temp, 0)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
2058  (Te[1][GETBYTE(temp, 3)] & 0x000000ff) ^
2059  rcon[i];
2060  rk[ 9] = rk[ 1] ^ rk[ 8];
2061  rk[10] = rk[ 2] ^ rk[ 9];
2062  rk[11] = rk[ 3] ^ rk[10];
2063  if (++i == 7)
2064  break;
2065  temp = rk[11];
2066  rk[12] = rk[ 4] ^
2067  (Te[2][GETBYTE(temp, 3)] & 0xff000000) ^
2068  (Te[3][GETBYTE(temp, 2)] & 0x00ff0000) ^
2069  (Te[0][GETBYTE(temp, 1)] & 0x0000ff00) ^
2070  (Te[1][GETBYTE(temp, 0)] & 0x000000ff);
2071  rk[13] = rk[ 5] ^ rk[12];
2072  rk[14] = rk[ 6] ^ rk[13];
2073  rk[15] = rk[ 7] ^ rk[14];
2074 
2075  rk += 8;
2076  }
2077  break;
2078  #endif /* 256 */
2079 
2080  default:
2081  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2082  } /* switch */
2083 
2084  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
2085  if (dir == AES_DECRYPTION) {
2086  unsigned int j;
2087  rk = aes->key;
2088 
2089  /* invert the order of the round keys: */
2090  for (i = 0, j = 4* aes->rounds; i < j; i += 4, j -= 4) {
2091  temp = rk[i ]; rk[i ] = rk[j ]; rk[j ] = temp;
2092  temp = rk[i + 1]; rk[i + 1] = rk[j + 1]; rk[j + 1] = temp;
2093  temp = rk[i + 2]; rk[i + 2] = rk[j + 2]; rk[j + 2] = temp;
2094  temp = rk[i + 3]; rk[i + 3] = rk[j + 3]; rk[j + 3] = temp;
2095  }
2096  /* apply the inverse MixColumn transform to all round keys but the
2097  first and the last: */
2098  for (i = 1; i < aes->rounds; i++) {
2099  rk += 4;
2100  rk[0] =
2101  Td[0][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[0], 3)] & 0xff] ^
2102  Td[1][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[0], 2)] & 0xff] ^
2103  Td[2][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[0], 1)] & 0xff] ^
2104  Td[3][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[0], 0)] & 0xff];
2105  rk[1] =
2106  Td[0][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[1], 3)] & 0xff] ^
2107  Td[1][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[1], 2)] & 0xff] ^
2108  Td[2][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[1], 1)] & 0xff] ^
2109  Td[3][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[1], 0)] & 0xff];
2110  rk[2] =
2111  Td[0][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[2], 3)] & 0xff] ^
2112  Td[1][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[2], 2)] & 0xff] ^
2113  Td[2][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[2], 1)] & 0xff] ^
2114  Td[3][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[2], 0)] & 0xff];
2115  rk[3] =
2116  Td[0][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[3], 3)] & 0xff] ^
2117  Td[1][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[3], 2)] & 0xff] ^
2118  Td[2][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[3], 1)] & 0xff] ^
2119  Td[3][Te[1][GETBYTE(rk[3], 0)] & 0xff];
2120  }
2121  }
2122  #else
2123  (void)dir;
2124  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
2125 #else
2126  (void)dir;
2127 #endif /* NEED_AES_TABLES */
2128 
2129  return wc_AesSetIV(aes, iv);
2130  }
2131 
2132  int wc_AesSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
2133  const byte* iv, int dir)
2134  {
2135  #if defined(AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE)
2136  const word32 max_key_len = (AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE / 8);
2137  #endif
2138 
2139  if (aes == NULL ||
2140  !((keylen == 16) || (keylen == 24) || (keylen == 32))) {
2141  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2142  }
2143 
2144  #if defined(AES_MAX_KEY_SIZE)
2145  /* Check key length */
2146  if (keylen > max_key_len) {
2147  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2148  }
2149  #endif
2150  aes->keylen = keylen;
2151  aes->rounds = keylen/4 + 6;
2152 
2153  #if defined(WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT) && defined(WC_ASYNC_ENABLE_AES)
2154  if (aes->asyncDev.marker == WOLFSSL_ASYNC_MARKER_AES) {
2155  XMEMCPY(aes->asyncKey, userKey, keylen);
2156  if (iv)
2157  XMEMCPY(aes->asyncIv, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2158  }
2159  #endif /* WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT */
2160 
2161  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
2162  if (checkAESNI == 0) {
2163  haveAESNI = Check_CPU_support_AES();
2164  checkAESNI = 1;
2165  }
2166  if (haveAESNI) {
2167  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER
2168  aes->left = 0;
2169  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER */
2170  aes->use_aesni = 1;
2171  if (iv)
2172  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2173  if (dir == AES_ENCRYPTION)
2174  return AES_set_encrypt_key(userKey, keylen * 8, aes);
2175  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
2176  else
2177  return AES_set_decrypt_key(userKey, keylen * 8, aes);
2178  #endif
2179  }
2180  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AESNI */
2181 
2182  return wc_AesSetKeyLocal(aes, userKey, keylen, iv, dir);
2183  }
2184 
2185  #if defined(WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT) || defined(WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER)
2186  /* AES-CTR and AES-DIRECT need to use this for key setup, no aesni yet */
2187  int wc_AesSetKeyDirect(Aes* aes, const byte* userKey, word32 keylen,
2188  const byte* iv, int dir)
2189  {
2190  return wc_AesSetKeyLocal(aes, userKey, keylen, iv, dir);
2191  }
2192  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_DIRECT || WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER */
2193 #endif /* wc_AesSetKey block */
2194 
2195 
2196 /* wc_AesSetIV is shared between software and hardware */
2197 int wc_AesSetIV(Aes* aes, const byte* iv)
2198 {
2199  if (aes == NULL)
2200  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2201 
2202  if (iv)
2203  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2204  else
2205  XMEMSET(aes->reg, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2206 
2207 #ifdef WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT
2208  XMEMCPY(aes->iv_ce, aes->reg, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2209 #endif
2210 
2211  return 0;
2212 }

2367 /* AES-CBC */
2368 #ifdef HAVE_AES_CBC
2369 #if defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
2370 
2371 #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
2372  int wc_AesCbcEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
2373  {
2374  int ret = 0;
2375  word32 blocks = (sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2376  CRYP_HandleTypeDef hcryp;
2377 
2378  XMEMSET(&hcryp, 0, sizeof(CRYP_HandleTypeDef));
2379  switch (aes->rounds) {
2380  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
2381  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_128B;
2382  break;
2383  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
2384  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;
2385  break;
2386  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
2387  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_256B;
2388  break;
2389  default:
2390  break;
2391  }
2392  hcryp.Instance = CRYP;
2393  hcryp.Init.DataType = CRYP_DATATYPE_8B;
2394  hcryp.Init.pKey = (uint8_t*)aes->key;
2395  hcryp.Init.pInitVect = (uint8_t*)aes->reg;
2396 
2397  HAL_CRYP_Init(&hcryp);
2398 
2399  while (blocks--) {
2400  if (HAL_CRYP_AESCBC_Encrypt(&hcryp, (uint8_t*)in, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
2401  out, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT) != HAL_OK) {
2402  ret = WC_TIMEOUT_E;
2403  break;
2404  }
2405 
2406  /* store iv for next call */
2407  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, out + sz - AES_BLOCK_SIZE, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2408 
2409  sz -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2410  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2411  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2412  }
2413 
2414  HAL_CRYP_DeInit(&hcryp);
2415 
2416  return ret;
2417  }
2418  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
2419  int wc_AesCbcDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
2420  {
2421  int ret = 0;
2422  word32 blocks = (sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2423  CRYP_HandleTypeDef hcryp;
2424 
2425  XMEMSET(&hcryp, 0, sizeof(CRYP_HandleTypeDef));
2426  switch (aes->rounds) {
2427  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
2428  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_128B;
2429  break;
2430  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
2431  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;
2432  break;
2433  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
2434  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_256B;
2435  break;
2436  default:
2437  break;
2438  }
2439  hcryp.Instance = CRYP;
2440  hcryp.Init.DataType = CRYP_DATATYPE_8B;
2441  hcryp.Init.pKey = (uint8_t*)aes->key;
2442  hcryp.Init.pInitVect = (uint8_t*)aes->reg;
2443 
2444  HAL_CRYP_Init(&hcryp);
2445 
2446  while (blocks--) {
2447  if (HAL_CRYP_AESCBC_Decrypt(&hcryp, (uint8_t*)in, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
2448  out, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT) != HAL_OK) {
2449  ret = WC_TIMEOUT_E;
2450  }
2451 
2452  /* store iv for next call */
2453  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, aes->tmp, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2454 
2455  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2456  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2457  }
2458 
2459  HAL_CRYP_DeInit(&hcryp);
2460 
2461  return ret;
2462  }
2463  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
2464 #else
2465  int wc_AesCbcEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
2466  {
2467  word32 *enc_key, *iv;
2468  word32 blocks = (sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2469  CRYP_InitTypeDef AES_CRYP_InitStructure;
2470  CRYP_KeyInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure;
2471  CRYP_IVInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure;
2472 
2473  enc_key = aes->key;
2474  iv = aes->reg;
2475 
2476  /* crypto structure initialization */
2477  CRYP_KeyStructInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
2478  CRYP_StructInit(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
2479  CRYP_IVStructInit(&AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure);
2480 
2481  /* reset registers to their default values */
2482  CRYP_DeInit();
2483 
2484  /* load key into correct registers */
2485  switch (aes->rounds) {
2486  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
2487  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_128b;
2488  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[0];
2489  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[1];
2490  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[2];
2491  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[3];
2492  break;
2493 
2494  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
2495  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_192b;
2496  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[0];
2497  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[1];
2498  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[2];
2499  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[3];
2500  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[4];
2501  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[5];
2502  break;
2503 
2504  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
2505  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_256b;
2506  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Left = enc_key[0];
2507  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Right = enc_key[1];
2508  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[2];
2509  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[3];
2510  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[4];
2511  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[5];
2512  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[6];
2513  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[7];
2514  break;
2515 
2516  default:
2517  break;
2518  }
2519  CRYP_KeyInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
2520 
2521  /* set iv */
2522  ByteReverseWords(iv, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2523  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV0Left = iv[0];
2524  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV0Right = iv[1];
2525  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV1Left = iv[2];
2526  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV1Right = iv[3];
2527  CRYP_IVInit(&AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure);
2528 
2529  /* set direction, mode, and datatype */
2530  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoDir = CRYP_AlgoDir_Encrypt;
2531  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoMode = CRYP_AlgoMode_AES_CBC;
2532  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_DataType = CRYP_DataType_8b;
2533  CRYP_Init(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
2534 
2535  /* enable crypto processor */
2536  CRYP_Cmd(ENABLE);
2537 
2538  while (blocks--) {
2539  /* flush IN/OUT FIFOs */
2540  CRYP_FIFOFlush();
2541 
2542  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[0]);
2543  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[4]);
2544  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[8]);
2545  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[12]);
2546 
2547  /* wait until the complete message has been processed */
2548  while (CRYP_GetFlagStatus(CRYP_FLAG_BUSY) != RESET) {}
2549 
2550  *(uint32_t*)&out[0] = CRYP_DataOut();
2551  *(uint32_t*)&out[4] = CRYP_DataOut();
2552  *(uint32_t*)&out[8] = CRYP_DataOut();
2553  *(uint32_t*)&out[12] = CRYP_DataOut();
2554 
2555  /* store iv for next call */
2556  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, out + sz - AES_BLOCK_SIZE, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2557 
2558  sz -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2559  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2560  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2561  }
2562 
2563  /* disable crypto processor */
2564  CRYP_Cmd(DISABLE);
2565 
2566  return 0;
2567  }
2568 
2569  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
2570  int wc_AesCbcDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
2571  {
2572  word32 *dec_key, *iv;
2573  word32 blocks = (sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2574  CRYP_InitTypeDef AES_CRYP_InitStructure;
2575  CRYP_KeyInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure;
2576  CRYP_IVInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure;
2577 
2578  dec_key = aes->key;
2579  iv = aes->reg;
2580 
2581  /* crypto structure initialization */
2582  CRYP_KeyStructInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
2583  CRYP_StructInit(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
2584  CRYP_IVStructInit(&AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure);
2585 
2586  /* if input and output same will overwrite input iv */
2587  XMEMCPY(aes->tmp, in + sz - AES_BLOCK_SIZE, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2588 
2589  /* reset registers to their default values */
2590  CRYP_DeInit();
2591 
2592  /* load key into correct registers */
2593  switch (aes->rounds) {
2594  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
2595  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_128b;
2596  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = dec_key[0];
2597  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = dec_key[1];
2598  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = dec_key[2];
2599  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = dec_key[3];
2600  break;
2601 
2602  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
2603  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_192b;
2604  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = dec_key[0];
2605  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = dec_key[1];
2606  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = dec_key[2];
2607  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = dec_key[3];
2608  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = dec_key[4];
2609  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = dec_key[5];
2610  break;
2611 
2612  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
2613  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_256b;
2614  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Left = dec_key[0];
2615  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Right = dec_key[1];
2616  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = dec_key[2];
2617  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = dec_key[3];
2618  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = dec_key[4];
2619  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = dec_key[5];
2620  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = dec_key[6];
2621  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = dec_key[7];
2622  break;
2623 
2624  default:
2625  break;
2626  }
2627 
2628  /* set direction, mode, and datatype for key preparation */
2629  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoDir = CRYP_AlgoDir_Decrypt;
2630  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoMode = CRYP_AlgoMode_AES_Key;
2631  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_DataType = CRYP_DataType_32b;
2632  CRYP_Init(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
2633  CRYP_KeyInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
2634 
2635  /* enable crypto processor */
2636  CRYP_Cmd(ENABLE);
2637 
2638  /* wait until key has been prepared */
2639  while (CRYP_GetFlagStatus(CRYP_FLAG_BUSY) != RESET) {}
2640 
2641  /* set direction, mode, and datatype for decryption */
2642  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoDir = CRYP_AlgoDir_Decrypt;
2643  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoMode = CRYP_AlgoMode_AES_CBC;
2644  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_DataType = CRYP_DataType_8b;
2645  CRYP_Init(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
2646 
2647  /* set iv */
2648  ByteReverseWords(iv, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2649 
2650  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV0Left = iv[0];
2651  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV0Right = iv[1];
2652  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV1Left = iv[2];
2653  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV1Right = iv[3];
2654  CRYP_IVInit(&AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure);
2655 
2656  /* enable crypto processor */
2657  CRYP_Cmd(ENABLE);
2658 
2659  while (blocks--) {
2660  /* flush IN/OUT FIFOs */
2661  CRYP_FIFOFlush();
2662 
2663  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[0]);
2664  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[4]);
2665  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[8]);
2666  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[12]);
2667 
2668  /* wait until the complete message has been processed */
2669  while (CRYP_GetFlagStatus(CRYP_FLAG_BUSY) != RESET) {}
2670 
2671  *(uint32_t*)&out[0] = CRYP_DataOut();
2672  *(uint32_t*)&out[4] = CRYP_DataOut();
2673  *(uint32_t*)&out[8] = CRYP_DataOut();
2674  *(uint32_t*)&out[12] = CRYP_DataOut();
2675 
2676  /* store iv for next call */
2677  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, aes->tmp, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2678 
2679  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2680  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2681  }
2682 
2683  /* disable crypto processor */
2684  CRYP_Cmd(DISABLE);
2685 
2686  return 0;
2687  }
2688  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
2689 #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
2690 
2691 #elif defined(HAVE_COLDFIRE_SEC)
2692  static int wc_AesCbcCrypt(Aes* aes, byte* po, const byte* pi, word32 sz,
2693  word32 descHeader)
2694  {
2695  #ifdef DEBUG_WOLFSSL
2696  int i; int stat1, stat2; int ret;
2697  #endif
2698 
2699  int size;
2700  volatile int v;
2701 
2702  if ((pi == NULL) || (po == NULL))
2703  return BAD_FUNC_ARG; /*wrong pointer*/
2704 
2705  wc_LockMutex(&Mutex_AesSEC);
2706 
2707  /* Set descriptor for SEC */
2708  secDesc->length1 = 0x0;
2709  secDesc->pointer1 = NULL;
2710 
2711  secDesc->length2 = AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2712  secDesc->pointer2 = (byte *)secReg; /* Initial Vector */
2713 
2714  switch(aes->rounds) {
2715  case 10: secDesc->length3 = 16; break;
2716  case 12: secDesc->length3 = 24; break;
2717  case 14: secDesc->length3 = 32; break;
2718  }
2719  XMEMCPY(secKey, aes->key, secDesc->length3);
2720 
2721  secDesc->pointer3 = (byte *)secKey;
2722  secDesc->pointer4 = AESBuffIn;
2723  secDesc->pointer5 = AESBuffOut;
2724  secDesc->length6 = 0x0;
2725  secDesc->pointer6 = NULL;
2726  secDesc->length7 = 0x0;
2727  secDesc->pointer7 = NULL;
2728  secDesc->nextDescriptorPtr = NULL;
2729 
2730  while (sz) {
2731  secDesc->header = descHeader;
2732  XMEMCPY(secReg, aes->reg, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2733  if ((sz % AES_BUFFER_SIZE) == sz) {
2734  size = sz;
2735  sz = 0;
2736  } else {
2737  size = AES_BUFFER_SIZE;
2738  sz -= AES_BUFFER_SIZE;
2739  }
2740  secDesc->length4 = size;
2741  secDesc->length5 = size;
2742 
2743  XMEMCPY(AESBuffIn, pi, size);
2744  if(descHeader == SEC_DESC_AES_CBC_DECRYPT) {
2745  XMEMCPY((void*)aes->tmp, (void*)&(pi[size-AES_BLOCK_SIZE]),
2746  AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2747  }
2748 
2749  /* Point SEC to the location of the descriptor */
2750  MCF_SEC_FR0 = (uint32)secDesc;
2751  /* Initialize SEC and wait for encryption to complete */
2752  MCF_SEC_CCCR0 = 0x0000001a;
2753  /* poll SISR to determine when channel is complete */
2754  v=0;
2755 
2756  while ((secDesc->header>> 24) != 0xff) v++;
2757 
2758  #ifdef DEBUG_WOLFSSL
2759  ret = MCF_SEC_SISRH;
2760  stat1 = MCF_SEC_AESSR;
2761  stat2 = MCF_SEC_AESISR;
2762  if (ret & 0xe0000000) {
2763  db_printf("Aes_Cbc(i=%d):ISRH=%08x, AESSR=%08x, "
2764  "AESISR=%08x\n", i, ret, stat1, stat2);
2765  }
2766  #endif
2767 
2768  XMEMCPY(po, AESBuffOut, size);
2769 
2770  if (descHeader == SEC_DESC_AES_CBC_ENCRYPT) {
2771  XMEMCPY((void*)aes->reg, (void*)&(po[size-AES_BLOCK_SIZE]),
2772  AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2773  } else {
2774  XMEMCPY((void*)aes->reg, (void*)aes->tmp, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2775  }
2776 
2777  pi += size;
2778  po += size;
2779  }
2780 
2781  wc_UnLockMutex(&Mutex_AesSEC);
2782  return 0;
2783  }
2784 
2785  int wc_AesCbcEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* po, const byte* pi, word32 sz)
2786  {
2787  return (wc_AesCbcCrypt(aes, po, pi, sz, SEC_DESC_AES_CBC_ENCRYPT));
2788  }
2789 
2790  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
2791  int wc_AesCbcDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* po, const byte* pi, word32 sz)
2792  {
2793  return (wc_AesCbcCrypt(aes, po, pi, sz, SEC_DESC_AES_CBC_DECRYPT));
2794  }
2795  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */

2799  {

2801  status_t status;
2802  byte *iv, *enc_key;

2804

2809  if (status != 0) {
2810  return status;
2811  }

2814  iv, enc_key, keySize);
2815  return (status == kStatus_Success) ? 0 : -1;

2840 #elif defined(FREESCALE_MMCAU)
2841  int wc_AesCbcEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
2842  {
2843  int i;
2844  int offset = 0;
2845  word32 blocks = (sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2846  byte *iv;
2847  byte temp_block[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
2848 
2849  iv = (byte*)aes->reg;
2850 
2851  while (blocks--) {
2852  XMEMCPY(temp_block, in + offset, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2853 
2854  /* XOR block with IV for CBC */
2855  for (i = 0; i < AES_BLOCK_SIZE; i++)
2856  temp_block[i] ^= iv[i];
2857 
2858  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, temp_block, out + offset);
2859 
2860  offset += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2861 
2862  /* store IV for next block */
2863  XMEMCPY(iv, out + offset - AES_BLOCK_SIZE, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2864  }
2865 
2866  return 0;
2867  }
2868  #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
2869  int wc_AesCbcDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
2870  {
2871  int i;
2872  int offset = 0;
2873  word32 blocks = (sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2874  byte* iv;
2875  byte temp_block[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
2876 
2877  iv = (byte*)aes->reg;
2878 
2879  while (blocks--) {
2880  XMEMCPY(temp_block, in + offset, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2881 
2882  wc_AesDecrypt(aes, in + offset, out + offset);
2883 
2884  /* XOR block with IV for CBC */
2885  for (i = 0; i < AES_BLOCK_SIZE; i++)
2886  (out + offset)[i] ^= iv[i];
2887 
2888  /* store IV for next block */
2889  XMEMCPY(iv, temp_block, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
2890 
2891  offset += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
2892  }
2893 
2894  return 0;
2895  }
2896  #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */

3031  int wc_AesCbcEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
3032  {
3033  int ret = 0;
3034  uint8_t* pKey;
3035 #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
3036  word32 key[4];
3037  ByteReverseWords(key, aes->key, 16);
3038  pKey = (uint8_t*)key;
3039 #else
3040  pKey = (uint8_t*)aes->key;
3041 #endif
3042 
3043  if (STATUS_SUCCESS != CSE_DRV_LoadPlainKey(pKey, 10))
3044  {
3045  return WC_TIMEOUT_E;
3046  }
3047 
3048  if (STATUS_SUCCESS != CSE_DRV_EncryptCBC(CSE_RAM_KEY, in, sz, (uint8_t*)aes->reg, out, CSE_TIMEOUT))
3049  {
3050  ret = WC_TIMEOUT_E;
3051  }
3052  /* store iv for next call */
3053  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, out + sz - AES_BLOCK_SIZE, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3054  return ret;
3055  }

3157 
3158  return 0;

3166

3295  switch (aes->rounds) {

3298  break;

3300  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;

3324  #else
3325  int wc_AesCtrEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
3326  {
3327  word32 *enc_key, *iv;
3328  int len = (int)sz;
3329 
3330  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL) {
3331  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3332  }
3333  CRYP_InitTypeDef AES_CRYP_InitStructure;
3334  CRYP_KeyInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure;
3335  CRYP_IVInitTypeDef AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure;
3336 
3337  enc_key = aes->key;
3338  iv = aes->reg;
3339 
3340  /* crypto structure initialization */
3341  CRYP_KeyStructInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
3342  CRYP_StructInit(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
3343  CRYP_IVStructInit(&AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure);
3344 
3345  /* reset registers to their default values */
3346  CRYP_DeInit();
3347 
3348  /* load key into correct registers */
3349  switch (aes->rounds) {
3350  case 10: /* 128-bit key */
3351  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_128b;
3352  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[0];
3353  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[1];
3354  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[2];
3355  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[3];
3356  break;
3357 
3358  case 12: /* 192-bit key */
3359  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_192b;
3360  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[0];
3361  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[1];
3362  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[2];
3363  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[3];
3364  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[4];
3365  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[5];
3366  break;
3367 
3368  case 14: /* 256-bit key */
3369  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_KeySize = CRYP_KeySize_256b;
3370  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Left = enc_key[0];
3371  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key0Right = enc_key[1];
3372  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Left = enc_key[2];
3373  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key1Right = enc_key[3];
3374  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Left = enc_key[4];
3375  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key2Right = enc_key[5];
3376  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Left = enc_key[6];
3377  AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure.CRYP_Key3Right = enc_key[7];
3378  break;
3379 
3380  default:
3381  break;
3382  }
3383  CRYP_KeyInit(&AES_CRYP_KeyInitStructure);
3384 
3385  /* set iv */
3386  ByteReverseWords(iv, iv, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3387  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV0Left = iv[0];
3388  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV0Right = iv[1];
3389  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV1Left = iv[2];
3390  AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure.CRYP_IV1Right = iv[3];
3391  CRYP_IVInit(&AES_CRYP_IVInitStructure);
3392 
3393  /* set direction, mode, and datatype */
3394  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoDir = CRYP_AlgoDir_Encrypt;
3395  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_AlgoMode = CRYP_AlgoMode_AES_CTR;
3396  AES_CRYP_InitStructure.CRYP_DataType = CRYP_DataType_8b;
3397  CRYP_Init(&AES_CRYP_InitStructure);
3398 
3399  /* enable crypto processor */
3400  CRYP_Cmd(ENABLE);
3401 
3402  while (len > 0) {
3403  /* flush IN/OUT FIFOs */
3404  CRYP_FIFOFlush();
3405 
3406  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[0]);
3407  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[4]);
3408  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[8]);
3409  CRYP_DataIn(*(uint32_t*)&in[12]);
3410 
3411  /* wait until the complete message has been processed */
3412  while (CRYP_GetFlagStatus(CRYP_FLAG_BUSY) != RESET) {}
3413 
3414  *(uint32_t*)&out[0] = CRYP_DataOut();
3415  *(uint32_t*)&out[4] = CRYP_DataOut();
3416  *(uint32_t*)&out[8] = CRYP_DataOut();
3417  *(uint32_t*)&out[12] = CRYP_DataOut();
3418 
3419  /* store iv for next call */
3420  XMEMCPY(aes->reg, out + len - AES_BLOCK_SIZE, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3421 
3422  len -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3423  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3424  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3425  }
3426 
3427  /* disable crypto processor */
3428  CRYP_Cmd(DISABLE);
3429  }

3432  #elif defined(WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT)
3433  static void Pic32AesIncIV(Aes* aes) {
3434  int i;
3435  for (i = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3436  if (++((byte *)aes->iv_ce)[i])
3437  break;
3438  }
3439  }
3440  int wc_AesCtrEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
3441  {
3442  int ret = 0;
3443  byte out_block[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
3444  int odd, even, blocks;
3445  byte *tmp;
3446 
3447  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL) {
3448  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3449  }
3450 
3451  tmp = (byte *)aes->tmp;
3452  if (aes->left) {
3453  if ((aes->left + sz) >= AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3454  odd = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - aes->left;
3455  } else {
3456  odd = sz;
3457  }
3458  XMEMCPY(tmp + aes->left, in, odd);
3459  if ((odd + aes->left) == AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3460  ret = wc_Pic32AesCrypt(
3461  aes->key_ce, aes->keylen, aes->iv_ce, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
3462  out_block, tmp, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
3463  PIC32_ENCRYPTION, PIC32_ALGO_AES, PIC32_CRYPTOALGO_RCTR);
3464  XMEMCPY(out, out_block + aes->left, odd);
3465  aes->left = 0;
3466  XMEMSET(tmp, 0x0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3467  Pic32AesIncIV(aes);
3468  }
3469  in += odd;
3470  out+= odd;
3471  sz -= odd;
3472  }
3473 
3474  blocks = sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3475  if (blocks) {
3476  even = blocks * AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3477  ret = wc_Pic32AesCrypt(
3478  aes->key_ce, aes->keylen, aes->iv_ce, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
3479  out, in, even,
3480  PIC32_ENCRYPTION, PIC32_ALGO_AES, PIC32_CRYPTOALGO_RCTR);
3481  out += even;
3482  in += even;
3483  do {
3484  Pic32AesIncIV(aes);
3485  even -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3486  } while (even > 0);
3487  }
3488 
3489  /* if there is tail fragment */
3490  odd = sz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3491  if (odd) {
3492  XMEMSET(tmp + aes->left, 0x0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE - aes->left);
3493  XMEMCPY(tmp + aes->left, in, odd);
3494  ret = wc_Pic32AesCrypt(
3495  aes->key_ce, aes->keylen, aes->iv_ce, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
3496  out_block, tmp, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
3497  PIC32_ENCRYPTION, PIC32_ALGO_AES, PIC32_CRYPTOALGO_RCTR);
3498  XMEMCPY(out, out_block + aes->left, odd);
3499  aes->left += odd;
3500  }
3501 
3502  return ret;
3503  }
3504 
3505  #elif defined(HAVE_COLDFIRE_SEC)
3506  #error "Coldfire SEC doesn't currently support AES-CTR mode"
3507 
3508  #elif defined(FREESCALE_LTC)
3509  int wc_AesCtrEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
3510  {
3511  uint32_t keySize;
3512  byte *iv, *enc_key;
3513  byte* tmp;
3514 
3515  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL) {
3516  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3517  }
3518  tmp = (byte*)aes->tmp + AES_BLOCK_SIZE - aes->left;
3519 
3520  /* consume any unused bytes left in aes->tmp */
3521  while (aes->left && sz) {
3522  *(out++) = *(in++) ^ *(tmp++);
3523  aes->left--;
3524  sz--;
3525  }
3526 
3527  if (sz) {
3528  iv = (byte*)aes->reg;
3529  enc_key = (byte*)aes->key;
3530 
3531  wc_AesGetKeySize(aes, &keySize);
3532 
3533  LTC_AES_CryptCtr(LTC_BASE, in, out, sz,
3534  iv, enc_key, keySize, (byte*)aes->tmp,
3535  (uint32_t*)&(aes->left));
3536  }
3537 
3538  return 0;
3539  }
3540 
3541  #else
3542  /* Increment AES counter */
3543  static INLINE void IncrementAesCounter(byte* inOutCtr)
3544  {
3545  int i;
3546 
3547  /* in network byte order so start at end and work back */
3548  for (i = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3549  if (++inOutCtr[i]) /* we're done unless we overflow */
3550  return;
3551  }
3552  }
3553 
3554  int wc_AesCtrEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz)
3555  {
3556  byte* tmp;
3557 
3558  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL) {
3559  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3560  }
3561  tmp = (byte*)aes->tmp + AES_BLOCK_SIZE - aes->left;
3562 
3563  /* consume any unused bytes left in aes->tmp */
3564  while (aes->left && sz) {
3565  *(out++) = *(in++) ^ *(tmp++);
3566  aes->left--;
3567  sz--;
3568  }
3569 
3570  /* do as many block size ops as possible */
3571  while (sz >= AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3572  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, (byte*)aes->reg, out);
3573  IncrementAesCounter((byte*)aes->reg);
3574  xorbuf(out, in, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3575 
3576  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3577  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3578  sz -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3579  aes->left = 0;
3580  }
3581 
3582  /* handle non block size remaining and store unused byte count in left */
3583  if (sz) {
3584  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, (byte*)aes->reg, (byte*)aes->tmp);
3585  IncrementAesCounter((byte*)aes->reg);
3586 
3587  aes->left = AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
3588  tmp = (byte*)aes->tmp;
3589 
3590  while (sz--) {
3591  *(out++) = *(in++) ^ *(tmp++);
3592  aes->left--;
3593  }
3594  }
3595 
3596  return 0;
3597  }
3598 
3599  #endif /* AES-CTR block */
3600 
3601 #endif /* WOLFSSL_AES_COUNTER */
3602 
3603 
3604 #ifdef HAVE_AESGCM
3605 
3606 /*
3607  * The IV for AES GCM, stored in struct Aes's member reg, is comprised of
3608  * three parts in order:
3609  * 1. The implicit IV. This is generated from the PRF using the shared
3610  * secrets between endpoints. It is 4 bytes long.
3611  * 2. The explicit IV. This is set by the user of the AES. It needs to be
3612  * unique for each call to encrypt. The explicit IV is shared with the
3613  * other end of the transaction in the clear.
3614  * 3. The counter. Each block of data is encrypted with its own sequence
3615  * number counter.
3616  */
3617 
3618 #if defined(HAVE_COLDFIRE_SEC)
3619  #error "Coldfire SEC doesn't currently support AES-GCM mode"
3620 
3621 #elif defined(WOLFSSL_NRF51_AES)
3622  #error "nRF51 doesn't currently support AES-GCM mode"
3623 
3624 #endif
3625 
3626 enum {
3627  NONCE_SZ = 12,
3628  CTR_SZ = 4
3629 };
3630 
3631 #if !defined(FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM)
3632 static INLINE void IncrementGcmCounter(byte* inOutCtr)
3633 {
3634  int i;
3635 
3636  /* in network byte order so start at end and work back */
3637  for (i = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1; i >= AES_BLOCK_SIZE - CTR_SZ; i--) {
3638  if (++inOutCtr[i]) /* we're done unless we overflow */
3639  return;
3640  }
3641 }
3642 #endif /* !FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM */
3643 
3644 #if defined(GCM_SMALL) || defined(GCM_TABLE)
3645 
3646 static INLINE void FlattenSzInBits(byte* buf, word32 sz)
3647 {
3648  /* Multiply the sz by 8 */
3649  word32 szHi = (sz >> (8*sizeof(sz) - 3));
3650  sz <<= 3;
3651 
3652  /* copy over the words of the sz into the destination buffer */
3653  buf[0] = (szHi >> 24) & 0xff;
3654  buf[1] = (szHi >> 16) & 0xff;
3655  buf[2] = (szHi >> 8) & 0xff;
3656  buf[3] = szHi & 0xff;
3657  buf[4] = (sz >> 24) & 0xff;
3658  buf[5] = (sz >> 16) & 0xff;
3659  buf[6] = (sz >> 8) & 0xff;
3660  buf[7] = sz & 0xff;
3661 }
3662 
3663 
3664 static INLINE void RIGHTSHIFTX(byte* x)
3665 {
3666  int i;
3667  int carryOut = 0;
3668  int carryIn = 0;
3669  int borrow = x[15] & 0x01;
3670 
3671  for (i = 0; i < AES_BLOCK_SIZE; i++) {
3672  carryOut = x[i] & 0x01;
3673  x[i] = (x[i] >> 1) | (carryIn ? 0x80 : 0);
3674  carryIn = carryOut;
3675  }
3676  if (borrow) x[0] ^= 0xE1;
3677 }
3678 
3679 #endif /* defined(GCM_SMALL) || defined(GCM_TABLE) */
3680 
3681 
3682 #ifdef GCM_TABLE
3683 
3684 static void GenerateM0(Aes* aes)
3685 {
3686  int i, j;
3687  byte (*m)[AES_BLOCK_SIZE] = aes->M0;
3688 
3689  XMEMCPY(m[128], aes->H, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3690 
3691  for (i = 64; i > 0; i /= 2) {
3692  XMEMCPY(m[i], m[i*2], AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3693  RIGHTSHIFTX(m[i]);
3694  }
3695 
3696  for (i = 2; i < 256; i *= 2) {
3697  for (j = 1; j < i; j++) {
3698  XMEMCPY(m[i+j], m[i], AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3699  xorbuf(m[i+j], m[j], AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3700  }
3701  }
3702 
3703  XMEMSET(m[0], 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3704 }
3705 
3706 #endif /* GCM_TABLE */
3707 
3708 
3709 int wc_AesGcmSetKey(Aes* aes, const byte* key, word32 len)
3710 {
3711  int ret;
3712  byte iv[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
3713 
3714  if (!((len == 16) || (len == 24) || (len == 32)))
3715  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3716 
3717  XMEMSET(iv, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
3718  ret = wc_AesSetKey(aes, key, len, iv, AES_ENCRYPTION);
3719 
3720  #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
3721  /* AES-NI code generates its own H value. */
3722  if (haveAESNI)
3723  return ret;
3724  #endif /* WOLFSSL_AESNI */
3725 
3726 #if !defined(FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM)
3727  if (ret == 0) {
3728  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, iv, aes->H);
3729  #ifdef GCM_TABLE
3730  GenerateM0(aes);
3731  #endif /* GCM_TABLE */
3732  }
3733 #endif /* FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM */
3734 
3735 #if defined(WOLFSSL_XILINX_CRYPT)
3736  wc_AesGcmSetKey_ex(aes, key, len, XSECURE_CSU_AES_KEY_SRC_KUP);
3737 #endif
3738 
3739  return ret;
3740 }

3743 #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
3744 
3745 #if defined(USE_INTEL_SPEEDUP)
3746  #define HAVE_INTEL_AVX1
3747  #define HAVE_INTEL_AVX2
3748 #endif /* USE_INTEL_SPEEDUP */
3749 
3750 static const __m128i MOD2_128 = { 0x1, 0xc200000000000000UL };
3751 
3752 static __m128i gfmul_sw(__m128i a, __m128i b)
3753 {
3754  __m128i r, t1, t2, t3, t4, t5, t6, t7;
3755 #ifndef WOLFSSL_AES_GCM_SLOW_CLMUL
3756  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
3757  t3 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x10);
3758  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x01);
3759  t1 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x00);
3760  t4 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x11);
3761  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, t2);
3762  t2 = _mm_slli_si128(t3, 8);
3763  t3 = _mm_srli_si128(t3, 8);
3764  t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, t2);
3765  t4 = _mm_xor_si128(t4, t3);
3766 
3767  /* shift left 1 bit - bits reversed */
3768  t5 = _mm_srli_epi32(t1, 31);
3769  t6 = _mm_srli_epi32(t4, 31);
3770  t1 = _mm_slli_epi32(t1, 1);
3771  t4 = _mm_slli_epi32(t4, 1);
3772  t7 = _mm_srli_si128(t5, 12);
3773  t5 = _mm_slli_si128(t5, 4);
3774  t6 = _mm_slli_si128(t6, 4);
3775  t4 = _mm_or_si128(t4, t7);
3776  t1 = _mm_or_si128(t1, t5);
3777  t4 = _mm_or_si128(t4, t6);
3778 
3779  /* Reduction */
3780  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(t1, MOD2_128, 0x10);
3781  t3 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(t1, 78);
3782  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, t2);
3783  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(t3, MOD2_128, 0x10);
3784  t3 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(t3, 78);
3785  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, t2);
3786  r = _mm_xor_si128(t4, t3);
3787 #else
3788  t2 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(b, 78);
3789  t3 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(a, 78);
3790  t2 = _mm_xor_si128(t2, b);
3791  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, a);
3792  t4 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(b, a, 0x11);
3793  t1 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(b, a, 0x00);
3794  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(t2, t3, 0x00);
3795  t2 = _mm_xor_si128(t2, t1);
3796  t2 = _mm_xor_si128(t2, t4);
3797  t3 = _mm_slli_si128(t2, 8);
3798  t2 = _mm_srli_si128(t2, 8);
3799  t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, t3);
3800  t4 = _mm_xor_si128(t4, t2);
3801 
3802  t5 = _mm_srli_epi32(t1, 31);
3803  t6 = _mm_srli_epi32(t4, 31);
3804  t1 = _mm_slli_epi32(t1, 1);
3805  t4 = _mm_slli_epi32(t4, 1);
3806  t7 = _mm_srli_si128(t5, 12);
3807  t5 = _mm_slli_si128(t5, 4);
3808  t6 = _mm_slli_si128(t6, 4);
3809  t4 = _mm_or_si128(t4, t7);
3810  t1 = _mm_or_si128(t1, t5);
3811  t4 = _mm_or_si128(t4, t6);
3812 
3813  t5 = _mm_slli_epi32(t1, 31);
3814  t6 = _mm_slli_epi32(t1, 30);
3815  t7 = _mm_slli_epi32(t1, 25);
3816  t5 = _mm_xor_si128(t5, t6);
3817  t5 = _mm_xor_si128(t5, t7);
3818 
3819  t6 = _mm_srli_si128(t5, 4);
3820  t5 = _mm_slli_si128(t5, 12);
3821  t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, t5);
3822  t7 = _mm_srli_epi32(t1, 1);
3823  t3 = _mm_srli_epi32(t1, 2);
3824  t2 = _mm_srli_epi32(t1, 7);
3825 
3826  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t3);
3827  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t2);
3828  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t6);
3829  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t1);
3830  r = _mm_xor_si128(t4, t7);
3831 #endif
3832 
3833  return r;
3834 }
3835 
3836 static void gfmul_only(__m128i a, __m128i b, __m128i* r0, __m128i* r1)
3837 {
3838  __m128i t1, t2, t3, t4;
3839 
3840  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
3841 #ifndef WOLFSSL_AES_GCM_SLOW_CLMUL
3842  t3 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x10);
3843  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x01);
3844  t1 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x00);
3845  t4 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(a, b, 0x11);
3846  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, t2);
3847  t2 = _mm_slli_si128(t3, 8);
3848  t3 = _mm_srli_si128(t3, 8);
3849  t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, t2);
3850  t4 = _mm_xor_si128(t4, t3);
3851 #else
3852  t2 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(b, 78);
3853  t3 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(a, 78);
3854  t2 = _mm_xor_si128(t2, b);
3855  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, a);
3856  t4 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(b, a, 0x11);
3857  t1 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(b, a, 0x00);
3858  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(t2, t3, 0x00);
3859  t2 = _mm_xor_si128(t2, t1);
3860  t2 = _mm_xor_si128(t2, t4);
3861  t3 = _mm_slli_si128(t2, 8);
3862  t2 = _mm_srli_si128(t2, 8);
3863  t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, t3);
3864  t4 = _mm_xor_si128(t4, t2);
3865 #endif
3866  *r0 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, *r0);
3867  *r1 = _mm_xor_si128(t4, *r1);
3868 }
3869 
3870 static __m128i gfmul_shl1(__m128i a)
3871 {
3872  __m128i t1 = a, t2;
3873  t2 = _mm_srli_epi64(t1, 63);
3874  t1 = _mm_slli_epi64(t1, 1);
3875  t2 = _mm_slli_si128(t2, 8);
3876  t1 = _mm_or_si128(t1, t2);
3877  /* if (a[1] >> 63) t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, MOD2_128); */
3878  a = _mm_shuffle_epi32(a, 0xff);
3879  a = _mm_srai_epi32(a, 31);
3880  a = _mm_and_si128(a, MOD2_128);
3881  t1 = _mm_xor_si128(t1, a);
3882  return t1;
3883 }
3884 
3885 static __m128i ghash_red(__m128i r0, __m128i r1)
3886 {
3887  __m128i t2, t3;
3888 #ifndef WOLFSSL_AES_GCM_SLOW_CLMUL
3889  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(r0, MOD2_128, 0x10);
3890  t3 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(r0, 78);
3891  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, t2);
3892  t2 = _mm_clmulepi64_si128(t3, MOD2_128, 0x10);
3893  t3 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(t3, 78);
3894  t3 = _mm_xor_si128(t3, t2);
3895  return _mm_xor_si128(r1, t3);
3896 #else
3897  __m128i t5, t6, t7;
3898 
3899  t5 = _mm_slli_epi32(r0, 31);
3900  t6 = _mm_slli_epi32(r0, 30);
3901  t7 = _mm_slli_epi32(r0, 25);
3902  t5 = _mm_xor_si128(t5, t6);
3903  t5 = _mm_xor_si128(t5, t7);
3904 
3905  t6 = _mm_srli_si128(t5, 4);
3906  t5 = _mm_slli_si128(t5, 12);
3907  r0 = _mm_xor_si128(r0, t5);
3908  t7 = _mm_srli_epi32(r0, 1);
3909  t3 = _mm_srli_epi32(r0, 2);
3910  t2 = _mm_srli_epi32(r0, 7);
3911 
3912  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t3);
3913  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t2);
3914  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, t6);
3915  t7 = _mm_xor_si128(t7, r0);
3916  return _mm_xor_si128(r1, t7);
3917 #endif
3918 }
3919 
3920 static __m128i gfmul_shifted(__m128i a, __m128i b)
3921 {
3922  __m128i t0 = _mm_setzero_si128(), t1 = _mm_setzero_si128();
3923  gfmul_only(a, b, &t0, &t1);
3924  return ghash_red(t0, t1);
3925 }

3927 #ifndef AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL
3928 static __m128i gfmul8(__m128i a1, __m128i a2, __m128i a3, __m128i a4,
3929  __m128i a5, __m128i a6, __m128i a7, __m128i a8,
3930  __m128i b1, __m128i b2, __m128i b3, __m128i b4,
3931  __m128i b5, __m128i b6, __m128i b7, __m128i b8)

3934  gfmul_only(a1, b8, &t0, &t1);
3935  gfmul_only(a2, b7, &t0, &t1);
3936  gfmul_only(a3, b6, &t0, &t1);
3937  gfmul_only(a4, b5, &t0, &t1);
3938  gfmul_only(a5, b4, &t0, &t1);
3939  gfmul_only(a6, b3, &t0, &t1);
3940  gfmul_only(a7, b2, &t0, &t1);
