3946 /* See Intel Carry-Less Multiplication Instruction
3947  * and its Usage for Computing the GCM Mode White Paper
3948  * by Shay Gueron, Intel Mobility Group, Israel Development Center;
3949  * and Michael E. Kounavis, Intel Labs, Circuits and Systems Research */
3950 
3951 
3952 /* Figure 9. AES-GCM Encrypt With Single Block Ghash at a Time */
3953 
3954 static const __m128i ONE = { 0x0, 0x1 };
3955 #ifndef AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL
3956 static const __m128i TWO = { 0x0, 0x2 };
3957 static const __m128i THREE = { 0x0, 0x3 };
3958 static const __m128i FOUR = { 0x0, 0x4 };
3959 static const __m128i FIVE = { 0x0, 0x5 };
3960 static const __m128i SIX = { 0x0, 0x6 };
3961 static const __m128i SEVEN = { 0x0, 0x7 };
3962 static const __m128i EIGHT = { 0x0, 0x8 };
3963 #endif
3964 static const __m128i BSWAP_EPI64 = { 0x0001020304050607, 0x08090a0b0c0d0e0f };
3965 static const __m128i BSWAP_MASK = { 0x08090a0b0c0d0e0f, 0x0001020304050607 };
3966 
3967 static void AES_GCM_encrypt(const unsigned char *in, unsigned char *out,
3968  const unsigned char* addt,
3969  const unsigned char* ivec,
3970  unsigned char *tag, unsigned int nbytes,
3971  unsigned int abytes, unsigned int ibytes,
3972  const unsigned char* key, int nr)
3973 {
3974  int i, j ,k;
3975  __m128i ctr1;
3976  __m128i H, Y, T;
3977  __m128i X = _mm_setzero_si128();
3978  __m128i *KEY = (__m128i*)key, lastKey;
3979  __m128i last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
3980  __m128i tmp1, tmp2;
3981 #ifndef AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL
3982  __m128i HT[8];
3983  __m128i r0, r1;
3984  __m128i XV;
3985  __m128i tmp3, tmp4, tmp5, tmp6, tmp7, tmp8;
3986 #endif
3987 
3988  if (ibytes == 12) {
3989  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
3990  for (j=0; j < 12; j++)
3991  ((unsigned char*)&Y)[j] = ivec[j];
3992  Y = _mm_insert_epi32(Y, 0x1000000, 3);
3993  /* (Compute E[ZERO, KS] and E[Y0, KS] together */
3994  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
3995  tmp2 = _mm_xor_si128(Y, KEY[0]);
3996  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
3997  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[1]);
3998  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
3999  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[2]);
4000  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
4001  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[3]);
4002  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
4003  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[4]);
4004  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
4005  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[5]);
4006  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
4007  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[6]);
4008  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
4009  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[7]);
4010  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
4011  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[8]);
4012  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
4013  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[9]);
4014  lastKey = KEY[10];
4015  if (nr > 10) {
4016  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4017  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
4018  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
4019  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[11]);
4020  lastKey = KEY[12];
4021  if (nr > 12) {
4022  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4023  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
4024  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
4025  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[13]);
4026  lastKey = KEY[14];
4027  }
4028  }
4029  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4030  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
4031  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);
4032  }
4033  else {
4034  if (ibytes % 16) {
4035  i = ibytes / 16;
4036  for (j=0; j < (int)(ibytes%16); j++)
4037  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = ivec[i*16+j];
4038  }
4039  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
4040  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
4041  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
4042  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
4043  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
4044  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
4045  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
4046  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
4047  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
4048  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
4049  lastKey = KEY[10];
4050  if (nr > 10) {
4051  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4052  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
4053  lastKey = KEY[12];
4054  if (nr > 12) {
4055  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4056  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
4057  lastKey = KEY[14];
4058  }
4059  }
4060  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4061  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);
4062  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
4063  for (i=0; i < (int)(ibytes/16); i++) {
4064  tmp1 = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)ivec)[i]);
4065  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
4066  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
4067  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
4068  }

4605  if (nbytes % 16) {

4615  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
4616  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
4617  lastKey = KEY[10];

4621  lastKey = KEY[12];

4629  last_block = tmp1;
4630  for (j=0; j < (int)(nbytes%16); j++)
4631  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = in[k*16+j];

4638  X =_mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
4639  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);

4643  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
4644  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);
4645  X = _mm_shuffle_epi8(X, BSWAP_MASK);
4646  T = _mm_xor_si128(X, T);
4647  _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)tag, T);
4648 }

4650 #ifdef HAVE_INTEL_AVX2
4651 static void AES_GCM_encrypt_avx2(const unsigned char *in, unsigned char *out,
4652  const unsigned char* addt,
4653  const unsigned char* ivec,
4654  unsigned char *tag, unsigned int nbytes,
4655  unsigned int abytes, unsigned int ibytes,
4656  const unsigned char* key, int nr)
4657 {
4658  int i, j ,k;
4659  __m128i ctr1;
4660  __m128i H, Y, T;
4661  __m128i X = _mm_setzero_si128();
4662  __m128i *KEY = (__m128i*)key, lastKey;
4663  __m128i last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
4664 #if !defined(AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL) && !defined(AES_GCM_AVX2_NO_UNROLL)
4665  __m128i HT[8];
4666  register __m128i tmp1 asm("xmm4");
4667  register __m128i tmp2 asm("xmm5");
4668  register __m128i tmp3 asm("xmm6");
4669  register __m128i tmp4 asm("xmm7");
4670  register __m128i tmp5 asm("xmm8");
4671  register __m128i tmp6 asm("xmm9");
4672  register __m128i tmp7 asm("xmm10");
4673  register __m128i tmp8 asm("xmm11");
4674  __m128i pctr1[1];
4675  register __m128i XV asm("xmm2");
4676 #else
4677  __m128i tmp1, tmp2;
4678 #endif
4679 
4680  if (ibytes == 12) {
4681  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
4682  for (j=0; j < 12; j++)
4683  ((unsigned char*)&Y)[j] = ivec[j];
4684  Y = _mm_insert_epi32(Y, 0x1000000, 3);
4685  /* (Compute E[ZERO, KS] and E[Y0, KS] together */
4686  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
4687  tmp2 = _mm_xor_si128(Y, KEY[0]);
4688  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
4689  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[1]);
4690  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
4691  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[2]);
4692  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
4693  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[3]);
4694  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
4695  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[4]);

4699  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[6]);

4701  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[7]);
4702  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
4703  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[8]);
4704  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
4705  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[9]);
4706  lastKey = KEY[10];
4707  if (nr > 10) {
4708  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4709  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
4710  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
4711  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[11]);
4712  lastKey = KEY[12];
4713  if (nr > 12) {

4715  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);

4717  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[13]);
4718  lastKey = KEY[14];
4719  }
4720  }
4721  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4722  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
4723  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);

4730  }

4786  lastKey = KEY[12];
4787  if (nr > 12) {

4789  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
4790  lastKey = KEY[14];
4791  }
4792  }
4793  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
4794  }
4795

4799  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
4800  X = gfmul_sw(X, H);
4801  }
4802  if (abytes%16) {
4803  last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();

4805  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = addt[i*16+j];
4806  tmp1 = last_block;
4807  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
4808  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
4809  X = gfmul_sw(X, H);
4810  }

4812  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(Y, BSWAP_EPI64);
4813  ctr1 = _mm_add_epi32(tmp1, ONE);
4814  H = gfmul_shl1(H);
4815 
4816 #if !defined(AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL) && !defined(AES_GCM_AVX2_NO_UNROLL)
4817  i = 0;
4818  if (nbytes >= 16*8) {
4819  HT[0] = H;

5496  "vaesenc 48(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5497  "vpclmulqdq $0, %[H], %[X], %%xmm15\n\t"
5498  "vaesenc 64(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5499  "vpclmulqdq $17, %[H], %[X], %%xmm1\n\t"
5500  "vaesenc 80(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5501  "vpxor %%xmm14, %%xmm13, %%xmm13\n\t"
5502  "vpslldq $8, %%xmm13, %%xmm2\n\t"
5503  "vpsrldq $8, %%xmm13, %%xmm13\n\t"
5504  "vaesenc 96(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5505  "vpxor %%xmm15, %%xmm2, %%xmm2\n\t"
5506  "vpxor %%xmm13, %%xmm1, %%xmm3\n\t"
5507  "vmovdqa %[MOD2_128], %%xmm0\n\t"
5508  "vpclmulqdq $16, %%xmm0, %%xmm2, %%xmm14\n\t"
5509  "vaesenc 112(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5510  "vpshufd $78, %%xmm2, %%xmm13\n\t"
5511  "vpxor %%xmm14, %%xmm13, %%xmm13\n\t"
5512  "vpclmulqdq $16, %%xmm0, %%xmm13, %%xmm14\n\t"
5513  "vaesenc 128(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5514  "vpshufd $78, %%xmm13, %%xmm13\n\t"
5515  "vpxor %%xmm14, %%xmm13, %%xmm13\n\t"
5516  "vpxor %%xmm3, %%xmm13, %%xmm13\n\t"
5517  "vaesenc 144(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5518  "vmovdqa %%xmm13, %[X]\n\t"
5519  "cmpl $11, %[nr]\n\t"
5520  "vmovaps 160(%[KEY]), %%xmm5\n\t"
5521  "jl %=f\n\t"
5522  "vaesenc %%xmm5, %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5523  "vaesenc 176(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5524  "cmpl $13, %[nr]\n\t"
5525  "vmovaps 192(%[KEY]), %%xmm5\n\t"
5526  "jl %=f\n\t"
5527  "vaesenc %%xmm5, %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5528  "vaesenc 208(%[KEY]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5529  "vmovaps 224(%[KEY]), %%xmm5\n\t"
5530  "%=:\n\t"
5531  "vaesenclast %%xmm5, %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5532  "vpxor (%[in]), %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5533  "vmovdqu %%xmm4, (%[out])\n\t"
5534  "vpshufb %[BSWAP_MASK], %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
5535  "vpxor %%xmm4, %[X], %[X]\n\t"
5536 
5537  : [H] "+xr" (H), [X] "+xr" (X),
5538  [ctr1] "+xr" (ctr1)
5539  : [KEY] "r" (KEY),
5540  [in] "r" (&in[k*16]), [out] "r" (&out[k*16]), [nr] "r" (nr),
5541  [BSWAP_MASK] "m" (BSWAP_MASK),
5542  [BSWAP_EPI64] "m" (BSWAP_EPI64),
5543  [ONE] "m" (ONE),
5544  [MOD2_128] "m" (MOD2_128)
5545  : "xmm15", "xmm14", "xmm13", "xmm4", "xmm5",
5546  "xmm0", "xmm1", "xmm2", "xmm3", "memory"
5547  );
5548  }
5549  if (k > 0) {
5550  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);
5551  }
5552 #endif
5553  /* If one partial block remains */
5554  if (nbytes % 16) {
5555  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(ctr1, BSWAP_EPI64);
5556  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, KEY[0]);
5557  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
5558  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
5559  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
5560  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
5561  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
5562  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
5563  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
5564  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
5565  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
5566  lastKey = KEY[10];
5567  if (nr > 10) {
5568  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5569  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
5570  lastKey = KEY[12];
5571  if (nr > 12) {
5572  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5573  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
5574  lastKey = KEY[14];
5575  }
5576  }
5577  tmp1 = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5578  last_block = tmp1;
5579  for (j=0; j < (int)(nbytes%16); j++)
5580  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = in[k*16+j];
5581  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, last_block);
5582  last_block = tmp1;
5583  for (j=0; j < (int)(nbytes%16); j++)
5584  out[k*16+j] = ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j];
5585  tmp1 = last_block;
5586  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
5587  X =_mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
5588  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);
5589  }
5590  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, nbytes*8, 0);
5591  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, abytes*8, 1);
5592  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
5593  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);
5594  X = _mm_shuffle_epi8(X, BSWAP_MASK);
5595  T = _mm_xor_si128(X, T);
5596  _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)tag, T);
5597 }
5598 #endif /* HAVE_INTEL_AVX2 */

5601 #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
5602 /* Figure 10. AES-GCM Decrypt With Single Block Ghash at a Time */
5603 
5604 static int AES_GCM_decrypt(const unsigned char *in, unsigned char *out,
5605  const unsigned char* addt, const unsigned char* ivec,
5606  const unsigned char *tag, int nbytes, int abytes,
5607  int ibytes, const unsigned char* key, int nr)
5608 {
5609  int i, j ,k;
5610  __m128i H, Y, T;
5611  __m128i *KEY = (__m128i*)key, lastKey;
5612  __m128i ctr1;
5613  __m128i last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
5614  __m128i X = _mm_setzero_si128();
5615  __m128i tmp1, tmp2, XV;
5616 #ifndef AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL
5617  __m128i HT[8];
5618  __m128i r0, r1;
5619  __m128i tmp3, tmp4, tmp5, tmp6, tmp7, tmp8;
5620 #endif
5621 
5622  if (ibytes == 12) {
5623  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
5624  for (j=0; j < 12; j++)
5625  ((unsigned char*)&Y)[j] = ivec[j];
5626  Y = _mm_insert_epi32(Y, 0x1000000, 3);
5627  /* (Compute E[ZERO, KS] and E[Y0, KS] together */
5628  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
5629  tmp2 = _mm_xor_si128(Y, KEY[0]);
5630  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
5631  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[1]);
5632  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
5633  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[2]);
5634  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
5635  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[3]);
5636  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
5637  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[4]);
5638  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
5639  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[5]);
5640  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
5641  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[6]);
5642  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
5643  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[7]);
5644  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
5645  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[8]);
5646  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
5647  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[9]);
5648  lastKey = KEY[10];
5649  if (nr > 10) {
5650  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5651  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
5652  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
5653  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[11]);
5654  lastKey = KEY[12];
5655  if (nr > 12) {
5656  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5657  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
5658  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
5659  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[13]);
5660  lastKey = KEY[14];
5661  }
5662  }
5663  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5664  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
5665  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);
5666  }
5667  else {
5668  if (ibytes % 16) {
5669  i = ibytes / 16;
5670  for (j=0; j < ibytes%16; j++)
5671  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = ivec[i*16+j];
5672  }
5673  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
5674  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
5675  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
5676  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
5677  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
5678  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
5679  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
5680  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
5681  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
5682  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
5683  lastKey = KEY[10];
5684  if (nr > 10) {
5685  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5686  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
5687  lastKey = KEY[12];
5688  if (nr > 12) {
5689  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5690  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
5691  lastKey = KEY[14];
5692  }
5693  }
5694  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5695  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);
5696 
5697  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
5698  for (i=0; i < ibytes/16; i++) {
5699  tmp1 = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)ivec)[i]);
5700  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
5701  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
5702  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
5703  }
5704  if (ibytes % 16) {
5705  tmp1 = last_block;
5706  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
5707  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
5708  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
5709  }
5710  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, ibytes*8, 0);
5711  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, 0, 1);
5712  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
5713  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
5714  Y = _mm_shuffle_epi8(Y, BSWAP_MASK); /* Compute E(K, Y0) */
5715  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(Y, KEY[0]);
5716  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
5717  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
5718  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
5719  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
5720  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
5721  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
5722  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
5723  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
5724  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
5725  lastKey = KEY[10];
5726  if (nr > 10) {
5727  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5728  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
5729  lastKey = KEY[12];
5730  if (nr > 12) {
5731  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5732  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
5733  lastKey = KEY[14];
5734  }
5735  }
5736  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5737  }
5738 
5739  for (i=0; i<abytes/16; i++) {
5740  tmp1 = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)addt)[i]);
5741  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
5742  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
5743  X = gfmul_sw(X, H);
5744  }
5745  if (abytes%16) {
5746  last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
5747  for (j=0; j<abytes%16; j++)
5748  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = addt[i*16+j];
5749  tmp1 = last_block;
5750  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
5751  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
5752  X = gfmul_sw(X, H);
5753  }
5754 
5755  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(Y, BSWAP_EPI64);
5756  ctr1 = _mm_add_epi32(tmp1, ONE);
5757  H = gfmul_shl1(H);
5758  i = 0;
5759 
5760 #ifndef AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL
5761 
5762  if (0 < nbytes/16/8) {
5763  HT[0] = H;
5764  HT[1] = gfmul_shifted(H, H);
5765  HT[2] = gfmul_shifted(H, HT[1]);
5766  HT[3] = gfmul_shifted(HT[1], HT[1]);
5767  HT[4] = gfmul_shifted(HT[1], HT[2]);
5768  HT[5] = gfmul_shifted(HT[2], HT[2]);
5769  HT[6] = gfmul_shifted(HT[2], HT[3]);
5770  HT[7] = gfmul_shifted(HT[3], HT[3]);
5771 
5772  for (; i < nbytes/16/8; i++) {
5773  r0 = _mm_setzero_si128();
5774  r1 = _mm_setzero_si128();
5775 
5776  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(ctr1, BSWAP_EPI64);
5777  tmp2 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, ONE);
5778  tmp2 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp2, BSWAP_EPI64);
5779  tmp3 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, TWO);
5780  tmp3 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp3, BSWAP_EPI64);
5781  tmp4 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, THREE);
5782  tmp4 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp4, BSWAP_EPI64);
5783  tmp5 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, FOUR);
5784  tmp5 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp5, BSWAP_EPI64);
5785  tmp6 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, FIVE);
5786  tmp6 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp6, BSWAP_EPI64);
5787  tmp7 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, SIX);
5788  tmp7 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp7, BSWAP_EPI64);
5789  tmp8 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, SEVEN);
5790  tmp8 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp8, BSWAP_EPI64);
5791  ctr1 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, EIGHT);
5792  tmp1 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp1, KEY[0]);
5793  tmp2 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp2, KEY[0]);
5794  tmp3 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp3, KEY[0]);
5795  tmp4 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp4, KEY[0]);
5796  tmp5 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp5, KEY[0]);
5797  tmp6 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp6, KEY[0]);
5798  tmp7 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp7, KEY[0]);
5799  tmp8 =_mm_xor_si128(tmp8, KEY[0]);
5800  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
5801  XV = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+0]);
5802  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
5803  XV = _mm_xor_si128(XV, X);
5804  gfmul_only(XV, HT[7], &r0, &r1);
5805  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
5806  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[1]);
5807  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[1]);
5808  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[1]);
5809  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[1]);
5810  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[1]);
5811  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[1]);
5812  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[1]);
5813  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
5814  XV = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+1]);
5815  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
5816  gfmul_only(XV, HT[6], &r0, &r1);
5817  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
5818  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[2]);
5819  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[2]);
5820  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[2]);
5821  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[2]);
5822  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[2]);
5823  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[2]);
5824  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[2]);
5825  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
5826  XV = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+2]);
5827  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
5828  gfmul_only(XV, HT[5], &r0, &r1);

5830  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[3]);

5839  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
5840  gfmul_only(XV, HT[4], &r0, &r1);
5841  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
5842  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[4]);
5843  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[4]);
5844  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[4]);
5845  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[4]);
5846  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[4]);
5847  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[4]);
5848  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[4]);

5887  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
5888  gfmul_only(XV, HT[0], &r0, &r1);
5889  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
5890  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[8]);
5891  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[8]);
5892  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[8]);
5893  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[8]);
5894  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[8]);
5895  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[8]);
5896  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[8]);
5897  /* Reduction */
5898  X = ghash_red(r0, r1);
5899  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
5900  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[9]);
5901  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[9]);
5902  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[9]);
5903  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[9]);
5904  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[9]);
5905  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[9]);
5906  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[9]);
5907  lastKey = KEY[10];
5908  if (nr > 10) {
5909  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[10]);
5910  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[10]);
5911  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[10]);
5912  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[10]);
5913  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[10]);
5914  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[10]);
5915  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[10]);
5916  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[10]);
5917  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
5918  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[11]);
5919  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[11]);
5920  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[11]);
5921  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[11]);
5922  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[11]);
5923  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[11]);
5924  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[11]);
5925  lastKey = KEY[12];
5926  if (nr > 12) {
5927  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[12]);
5928  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[12]);
5929  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[12]);
5930  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[12]);
5931  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[12]);
5932  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[12]);
5933  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[12]);
5934  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[12]);
5935  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
5936  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[13]);
5937  tmp3 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp3, KEY[13]);
5938  tmp4 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp4, KEY[13]);
5939  tmp5 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp5, KEY[13]);
5940  tmp6 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp6, KEY[13]);
5941  tmp7 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp7, KEY[13]);
5942  tmp8 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp8, KEY[13]);
5943  lastKey = KEY[14];
5944  }
5945  }
5946  tmp1 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5947  tmp2 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
5948  tmp3 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp3, lastKey);
5949  tmp4 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp4, lastKey);
5950  tmp5 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp5, lastKey);
5951  tmp6 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp6, lastKey);
5952  tmp7 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp7, lastKey);
5953  tmp8 =_mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp8, lastKey);
5954  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+0]));
5955  tmp2 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp2, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+1]));
5956  tmp3 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp3, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+2]));
5957  tmp4 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp4, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+3]));
5958  tmp5 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp5, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+4]));
5959  tmp6 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp6, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+5]));
5960  tmp7 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp7, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+6]));
5961  tmp8 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp8, _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[i*8+7]));
5962  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+0], tmp1);
5963  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+1], tmp2);
5964  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+2], tmp3);
5965  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+3], tmp4);
5966  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+4], tmp5);
5967  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+5], tmp6);
5968  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+6], tmp7);
5969  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[i*8+7], tmp8);
5970  }
5971  }
5972 #endif
5973  for (k = i*8; k < nbytes/16; k++) {
5974  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(ctr1, BSWAP_EPI64);
5975  ctr1 = _mm_add_epi32(ctr1, ONE);
5976  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, KEY[0]);
5977  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
5978  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
5979  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
5980  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
5981  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
5982  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
5983  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
5984  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
5985  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
5986  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
5987  XV = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[k]);
5988  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
5989  XV = _mm_xor_si128(XV, X);
5990  X = gfmul_shifted(XV, H);
5991  lastKey = KEY[10];
5992  if (nr > 10) {
5993  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5994  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
5995  lastKey = KEY[12];
5996  if (nr > 12) {
5997  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
5998  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
5999  lastKey = KEY[14];
6000  }
6001  }
6002  tmp1 = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6003  tmp2 = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)in)[k]);
6004  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, tmp2);
6005  _mm_storeu_si128(&((__m128i*)out)[k], tmp1);
6006  }
6007 
6008  /* If one partial block remains */
6009  if (nbytes % 16) {
6010  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(ctr1, BSWAP_EPI64);
6011  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, KEY[0]);
6012  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
6013  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
6014  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
6015  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
6016  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
6017  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
6018  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
6019  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
6020  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
6021  lastKey = KEY[10];
6022  if (nr > 10) {
6023  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6024  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
6025  lastKey = KEY[12];
6026  if (nr > 12) {
6027  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6028  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
6029  lastKey = KEY[14];
6030  }
6031  }
6032  tmp1 = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6033  last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
6034  for (j=0; j < nbytes%16; j++)
6035  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = in[k*16+j];
6036  XV = last_block;
6037  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, last_block);
6038  last_block = tmp1;
6039  for (j=0; j < nbytes%16; j++)
6040  out[k*16+j] = ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j];
6041  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
6042  XV = _mm_xor_si128(XV, X);
6043  X = gfmul_shifted(XV, H);
6044  }
6045 
6046  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, nbytes*8, 0);
6047  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, abytes*8, 1);
6048  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
6049  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
6050  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);
6051  X = _mm_shuffle_epi8(X, BSWAP_MASK);
6052  T = _mm_xor_si128(X, T);
6053 
6054  if (0xffff !=
6055  _mm_movemask_epi8(_mm_cmpeq_epi8(T, _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)tag))))
6056  return 0; /* in case the authentication failed */
6057 
6058  return 1; /* when successful returns 1 */
6059 }
6060 
6061 #ifdef HAVE_INTEL_AVX2
6062 static int AES_GCM_decrypt_avx2(const unsigned char *in, unsigned char *out,
6063  const unsigned char* addt,
6064  const unsigned char* ivec,
6065  const unsigned char *tag, int nbytes,
6066  int abytes, int ibytes,
6067  const unsigned char* key, int nr)
6068 {
6069  int i, j ,k;
6070  __m128i H, Y, T;
6071  __m128i *KEY = (__m128i*)key, lastKey;
6072  __m128i ctr1;
6073  __m128i last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
6074  __m128i X = _mm_setzero_si128();
6075  __m128i tmp1, tmp2;
6076 #if !defined(AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL) && !defined(AES_GCM_AVX2_NO_UNROLL)
6077  __m128i HT[8];
6078  __m128i pctr1[1];
6079  register __m128i XV asm("xmm2");
6080 #else
6081  __m128i XV;
6082 #endif
6083 
6084  if (ibytes == 12) {
6085  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
6086  for (j=0; j < 12; j++)
6087  ((unsigned char*)&Y)[j] = ivec[j];
6088  Y = _mm_insert_epi32(Y, 0x1000000, 3);
6089  /* (Compute E[ZERO, KS] and E[Y0, KS] together */
6090  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
6091  tmp2 = _mm_xor_si128(Y, KEY[0]);
6092  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
6093  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[1]);
6094  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
6095  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[2]);
6096  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
6097  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[3]);
6098  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
6099  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[4]);
6100  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
6101  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[5]);
6102  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
6103  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[6]);
6104  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
6105  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[7]);
6106  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
6107  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[8]);
6108  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
6109  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[9]);
6110  lastKey = KEY[10];
6111  if (nr > 10) {
6112  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6113  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
6114  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
6115  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[11]);
6116  lastKey = KEY[12];
6117  if (nr > 12) {
6118  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6119  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
6120  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
6121  tmp2 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp2, KEY[13]);
6122  lastKey = KEY[14];
6123  }
6124  }
6125  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6126  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp2, lastKey);
6127  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);
6128  }
6129  else {
6130  if (ibytes % 16) {
6131  i = ibytes / 16;
6132  for (j=0; j < ibytes%16; j++)
6133  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = ivec[i*16+j];
6134  }
6135  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(X, KEY[0]);
6136  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
6137  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
6138  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
6139  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
6140  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
6141  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
6142  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
6143  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
6144  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
6145  lastKey = KEY[10];
6146  if (nr > 10) {
6147  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6148  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
6149  lastKey = KEY[12];
6150  if (nr > 12) {
6151  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6152  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
6153  lastKey = KEY[14];
6154  }
6155  }
6156  H = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6157  H = _mm_shuffle_epi8(H, BSWAP_MASK);
6158 
6159  Y = _mm_setzero_si128();
6160  for (i=0; i < ibytes/16; i++) {
6161  tmp1 = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)ivec)[i]);
6162  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
6163  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
6164  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
6165  }
6166  if (ibytes % 16) {
6167  tmp1 = last_block;
6168  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
6169  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
6170  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
6171  }
6172  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, ibytes*8, 0);
6173  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, 0, 1);
6174  Y = _mm_xor_si128(Y, tmp1);
6175  Y = gfmul_sw(Y, H);
6176  Y = _mm_shuffle_epi8(Y, BSWAP_MASK); /* Compute E(K, Y0) */
6177  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(Y, KEY[0]);
6178  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
6179  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
6180  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
6181  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
6182  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
6183  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
6184  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
6185  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
6186  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
6187  lastKey = KEY[10];
6188  if (nr > 10) {
6189  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6190  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
6191  lastKey = KEY[12];
6192  if (nr > 12) {
6193  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6194  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
6195  lastKey = KEY[14];
6196  }
6197  }
6198  T = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6199  }
6200 
6201  for (i=0; i<abytes/16; i++) {
6202  tmp1 = _mm_loadu_si128(&((__m128i*)addt)[i]);
6203  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
6204  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
6205  X = gfmul_sw(X, H);
6206  }
6207  if (abytes%16) {
6208  last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
6209  for (j=0; j<abytes%16; j++)
6210  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = addt[i*16+j];
6211  tmp1 = last_block;
6212  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(tmp1, BSWAP_MASK);
6213  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
6214  X = gfmul_sw(X, H);
6215  }
6216 
6217  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(Y, BSWAP_EPI64);
6218  ctr1 = _mm_add_epi32(tmp1, ONE);
6219  H = gfmul_shl1(H);
6220  i = 0;
6221 
6222 #if !defined(AES_GCM_AESNI_NO_UNROLL) && !defined(AES_GCM_AVX2_NO_UNROLL)
6223 
6224  if (0 < nbytes/16/8) {
6225  HT[0] = H;
6226  HT[1] = gfmul_shifted(H, H);
6227  HT[2] = gfmul_shifted(H, HT[1]);
6228  HT[3] = gfmul_shifted(HT[1], HT[1]);
6229  HT[4] = gfmul_shifted(HT[1], HT[2]);
6230  HT[5] = gfmul_shifted(HT[2], HT[2]);
6231  HT[6] = gfmul_shifted(HT[2], HT[3]);
6232  HT[7] = gfmul_shifted(HT[3], HT[3]);
6233 
6234  pctr1[0] = ctr1;
6235  XV = X;
6236  for (; i < nbytes/16/8; i++) {
6237  __asm__ __volatile__ (
6238  "vmovaps (%[pctr1]), %%xmm0\n\t"
6239  "vmovaps %[BSWAP_EPI64], %%xmm1\n\t"
6240  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm0, %%xmm4\n\t"
6241  "vpaddd %[ONE], %%xmm0, %%xmm5\n\t"
6242  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm5, %%xmm5\n\t"
6243  "vpaddd %[TWO], %%xmm0, %%xmm6\n\t"
6244  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm6, %%xmm6\n\t"
6245  "vpaddd %[THREE], %%xmm0, %%xmm7\n\t"
6246  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm7, %%xmm7\n\t"
6247  "vpaddd %[FOUR], %%xmm0, %%xmm8\n\t"
6248  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm8, %%xmm8\n\t"
6249  "vpaddd %[FIVE], %%xmm0, %%xmm9\n\t"
6250  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm9, %%xmm9\n\t"
6251  "vpaddd %[SIX], %%xmm0, %%xmm10\n\t"
6252  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm10, %%xmm10\n\t"
6253  "vpaddd %[SEVEN], %%xmm0, %%xmm11\n\t"
6254  "vpshufb %%xmm1, %%xmm11, %%xmm11\n\t"
6255  "vpaddd %[EIGHT], %%xmm0, %%xmm0\n\t"
6256 
6257  "vmovaps (%[KEY]), %%xmm1\n\t"
6258  "vmovaps %%xmm0, (%[pctr1])\n\t"
6259  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
6260  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm5, %%xmm5\n\t"
6261  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm6, %%xmm6\n\t"
6262  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm7, %%xmm7\n\t"
6263  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm8, %%xmm8\n\t"
6264  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm9, %%xmm9\n\t"
6265  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm10, %%xmm10\n\t"
6266  "vpxor %%xmm1, %%xmm11, %%xmm11\n\t"
6267 
6268  "vmovaps 16(%[KEY]), %%xmm12\n\t"
6269  "vmovdqu (%[in]), %%xmm1\n\t"
6270  "vaesenc %%xmm12, %%xmm4, %%xmm4\n\t"
6271  "vmovaps 112(%[HT]), %%xmm0\n\t"
6272  "vpshufb %[BSWAP_MASK], %%xmm1, %%xmm1\n\t"
6273  "vpxor %[XV], %%xmm1, %%xmm1\n\t"
6274  "vaesenc %%xmm12, %%xmm5, %%xmm5\n\t"
6275  "vpclmulqdq $16, %%xmm1, %%xmm0, %%xmm13\n\t"
6276  "vaesenc %%xmm12, %%xmm6, %%xmm6\n\t"
6277  "vpclmulqdq $1, %%xmm1, %%xmm0, %%xmm14\n\t"
6278  "vaesenc %%xmm12, %%xmm7, %%xmm7\n\t"
6279  "vpclmulqdq $0, %%xmm1, %%xmm0, %%xmm15\n\t"
6280  "vaesenc %%xmm12, %%xmm8, %%xmm8\n\t"
6281  "vpclmulqdq $17, %%xmm1, %%xmm0, %%xmm1\n\t"
6282  "vaesenc %%xmm12, %%xmm9, %%xmm9\n\t"

6622  [ctr1] "+xr" (ctr1)
6623  : [KEY] "r" (KEY),
6624  [in] "r" (&in[k*16]), [out] "r" (&out[k*16]), [nr] "r" (nr),
6625  [BSWAP_MASK] "m" (BSWAP_MASK),
6626  [BSWAP_EPI64] "m" (BSWAP_EPI64),
6627  [ONE] "m" (ONE),
6628  [MOD2_128] "m" (MOD2_128)
6629  : "xmm15", "xmm14", "xmm13", "xmm4", "xmm5",
6630  "xmm0", "xmm1", "xmm2", "xmm3", "memory"
6631  );
6632  }
6633 
6634  /* If one partial block remains */
6635  if (nbytes % 16) {
6636  tmp1 = _mm_shuffle_epi8(ctr1, BSWAP_EPI64);
6637  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, KEY[0]);
6638  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[1]);
6639  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[2]);
6640  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[3]);
6641  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[4]);
6642  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[5]);
6643  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[6]);
6644  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[7]);
6645  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[8]);
6646  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[9]);
6647  lastKey = KEY[10];
6648  if (nr > 10) {
6649  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6650  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[11]);
6651  lastKey = KEY[12];
6652  if (nr > 12) {
6653  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6654  tmp1 = _mm_aesenc_si128(tmp1, KEY[13]);
6655  lastKey = KEY[14];
6656  }
6657  }
6658  tmp1 = _mm_aesenclast_si128(tmp1, lastKey);
6659  last_block = _mm_setzero_si128();
6660  for (j=0; j < nbytes%16; j++)
6661  ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j] = in[k*16+j];
6662  XV = last_block;
6663  tmp1 = _mm_xor_si128(tmp1, last_block);
6664  last_block = tmp1;
6665  for (j=0; j < nbytes%16; j++)
6666  out[k*16+j] = ((unsigned char*)&last_block)[j];
6667  XV = _mm_shuffle_epi8(XV, BSWAP_MASK);
6668  XV = _mm_xor_si128(XV, X);
6669  X = gfmul_shifted(XV, H);
6670  }
6671 
6672  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, nbytes*8, 0);
6673  tmp1 = _mm_insert_epi64(tmp1, abytes*8, 1);
6674  /* 128 x 128 Carryless Multiply */
6675  X = _mm_xor_si128(X, tmp1);
6676  X = gfmul_shifted(X, H);
6677  X = _mm_shuffle_epi8(X, BSWAP_MASK);
6678  T = _mm_xor_si128(X, T);
6679 
6680  if (0xffff !=
6681  _mm_movemask_epi8(_mm_cmpeq_epi8(T, _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)tag))))
6682  return 0; /* in case the authentication failed */
6683 
6684  return 1; /* when successful returns 1 */
6685 }
6686 #endif /* HAVE_INTEL_AVX2 */
6687 #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
6688 #endif /* WOLFSSL_AESNI */

6691 #if defined(GCM_SMALL)
6692 static void GMULT(byte* X, byte* Y)
6693 {
6694  byte Z[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
6695  byte V[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
6696  int i, j;
6697 
6698  XMEMSET(Z, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6699  XMEMCPY(V, X, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6700  for (i = 0; i < AES_BLOCK_SIZE; i++)
6701  {
6702  byte y = Y[i];
6703  for (j = 0; j < 8; j++)
6704  {
6705  if (y & 0x80) {
6706  xorbuf(Z, V, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6707  }
6708 
6709  RIGHTSHIFTX(V);
6710  y = y << 1;
6711  }
6712  }
6713  XMEMCPY(X, Z, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6714 }

6717 void GHASH(Aes* aes, const byte* a, word32 aSz, const byte* c,
6718  word32 cSz, byte* s, word32 sSz)
6719 {
6720  byte x[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
6721  byte scratch[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
6722  word32 blocks, partial;
6723  byte* h = aes->H;
6724 
6725  XMEMSET(x, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6726 
6727  /* Hash in A, the Additional Authentication Data */
6728  if (aSz != 0 && a != NULL) {
6729  blocks = aSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6730  partial = aSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6731  while (blocks--) {
6732  xorbuf(x, a, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6733  GMULT(x, h);
6734  a += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6735  }
6736  if (partial != 0) {
6737  XMEMSET(scratch, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6738  XMEMCPY(scratch, a, partial);
6739  xorbuf(x, scratch, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6740  GMULT(x, h);
6741  }
6742  }
6743 
6744  /* Hash in C, the Ciphertext */
6745  if (cSz != 0 && c != NULL) {
6746  blocks = cSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6747  partial = cSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6748  while (blocks--) {
6749  xorbuf(x, c, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6750  GMULT(x, h);
6751  c += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6752  }
6753  if (partial != 0) {
6754  XMEMSET(scratch, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6755  XMEMCPY(scratch, c, partial);
6756  xorbuf(x, scratch, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6757  GMULT(x, h);
6758  }
6759  }
6760 
6761  /* Hash in the lengths of A and C in bits */
6762  FlattenSzInBits(&scratch[0], aSz);
6763  FlattenSzInBits(&scratch[8], cSz);
6764  xorbuf(x, scratch, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6765  GMULT(x, h);
6766 
6767  /* Copy the result into s. */
6768  XMEMCPY(s, x, sSz);
6769 }

6841 static void GMULT(byte *x, byte m[256][AES_BLOCK_SIZE])
6842 {
6843  int i, j;
6844  byte Z[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
6845  byte a;
6846 
6847  XMEMSET(Z, 0, sizeof(Z));
6848 
6849  for (i = 15; i > 0; i--) {
6850  xorbuf(Z, m[x[i]], AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6851  a = Z[15];
6852 
6853  for (j = 15; j > 0; j--) {
6854  Z[j] = Z[j-1];
6855  }
6856 
6857  Z[0] = R[a][0];
6858  Z[1] ^= R[a][1];
6859  }
6860  xorbuf(Z, m[x[0]], AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6861 
6862  XMEMCPY(x, Z, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6863 }

6877  blocks = aSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6878  partial = aSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6879  while (blocks--) {
6880  xorbuf(x, a, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6881  GMULT(x, aes->M0);
6882  a += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6883  }

6885  XMEMSET(scratch, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);

6888  GMULT(x, aes->M0);

6895  partial = cSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6896  while (blocks--) {

6899  c += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6900  }

6905  GMULT(x, aes->M0);

6922 #if !defined(FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM)
6923 static void GMULT(word64* X, word64* Y)
6924 {
6925  word64 Z[2] = {0,0};
6926  word64 V[2];
6927  int i, j;
6928  V[0] = X[0]; V[1] = X[1];
6929 
6930  for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
6931  {
6932  word64 y = Y[i];
6933  for (j = 0; j < 64; j++)
6934  {
6935  if (y & 0x8000000000000000ULL) {
6936  Z[0] ^= V[0];
6937  Z[1] ^= V[1];
6938  }
6939 
6940  if (V[1] & 0x0000000000000001) {
6941  V[1] >>= 1;
6942  V[1] |= ((V[0] & 0x0000000000000001) ?
6943  0x8000000000000000ULL : 0);
6944  V[0] >>= 1;
6945  V[0] ^= 0xE100000000000000ULL;
6946  }
6947  else {
6948  V[1] >>= 1;
6949  V[1] |= ((V[0] & 0x0000000000000001) ?
6950  0x8000000000000000ULL : 0);
6951  V[0] >>= 1;
6952  }
6953  y <<= 1;
6954  }
6955  }
6956  X[0] = Z[0];
6957  X[1] = Z[1];
6958 }

6961 void GHASH(Aes* aes, const byte* a, word32 aSz, const byte* c,
6962  word32 cSz, byte* s, word32 sSz)
6963 {
6964  word64 x[2] = {0,0};
6965  word32 blocks, partial;
6966  word64 bigH[2];
6967 
6968  XMEMCPY(bigH, aes->H, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6969  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
6970  ByteReverseWords64(bigH, bigH, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6971  #endif
6972 
6973  /* Hash in A, the Additional Authentication Data */
6974  if (aSz != 0 && a != NULL) {
6975  word64 bigA[2];
6976  blocks = aSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6977  partial = aSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6978  while (blocks--) {
6979  XMEMCPY(bigA, a, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6980  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
6981  ByteReverseWords64(bigA, bigA, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6982  #endif
6983  x[0] ^= bigA[0];
6984  x[1] ^= bigA[1];
6985  GMULT(x, bigH);
6986  a += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
6987  }
6988  if (partial != 0) {
6989  XMEMSET(bigA, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6990  XMEMCPY(bigA, a, partial);
6991  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
6992  ByteReverseWords64(bigA, bigA, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
6993  #endif
6994  x[0] ^= bigA[0];
6995  x[1] ^= bigA[1];
6996  GMULT(x, bigH);
6997  }
6998  }
6999 
7000  /* Hash in C, the Ciphertext */
7001  if (cSz != 0 && c != NULL) {
7002  word64 bigC[2];
7003  blocks = cSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7004  partial = cSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7005  while (blocks--) {
7006  XMEMCPY(bigC, c, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7007  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7008  ByteReverseWords64(bigC, bigC, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7009  #endif
7010  x[0] ^= bigC[0];
7011  x[1] ^= bigC[1];
7012  GMULT(x, bigH);
7013  c += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7014  }
7015  if (partial != 0) {
7016  XMEMSET(bigC, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7017  XMEMCPY(bigC, c, partial);
7018  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7019  ByteReverseWords64(bigC, bigC, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7020  #endif
7021  x[0] ^= bigC[0];
7022  x[1] ^= bigC[1];
7023  GMULT(x, bigH);
7024  }
7025  }
7026 
7027  /* Hash in the lengths in bits of A and C */
7028  {
7029  word64 len[2];
7030  len[0] = aSz; len[1] = cSz;
7031 
7032  /* Lengths are in bytes. Convert to bits. */
7033  len[0] *= 8;
7034  len[1] *= 8;
7035 
7036  x[0] ^= len[0];
7037  x[1] ^= len[1];
7038  GMULT(x, bigH);
7039  }
7040  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7041  ByteReverseWords64(x, x, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7042  #endif
7043  XMEMCPY(s, x, sSz);
7044 }
7045 #endif /* !FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM */

7047 /* end defined(WORD64_AVAILABLE) && !defined(GCM_WORD32) */
7048 #else /* GCM_WORD32 */
7049 
7050 static void GMULT(word32* X, word32* Y)
7051 {
7052  word32 Z[4] = {0,0,0,0};
7053  word32 V[4];
7054  int i, j;
7055 
7056  V[0] = X[0]; V[1] = X[1]; V[2] = X[2]; V[3] = X[3];
7057 
7058  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
7059  {
7060  word32 y = Y[i];
7061  for (j = 0; j < 32; j++)
7062  {
7063  if (y & 0x80000000) {
7064  Z[0] ^= V[0];
7065  Z[1] ^= V[1];
7066  Z[2] ^= V[2];
7067  Z[3] ^= V[3];
7068  }
7069 
7070  if (V[3] & 0x00000001) {
7071  V[3] >>= 1;
7072  V[3] |= ((V[2] & 0x00000001) ? 0x80000000 : 0);
7073  V[2] >>= 1;
7074  V[2] |= ((V[1] & 0x00000001) ? 0x80000000 : 0);
7075  V[1] >>= 1;
7076  V[1] |= ((V[0] & 0x00000001) ? 0x80000000 : 0);
7077  V[0] >>= 1;
7078  V[0] ^= 0xE1000000;
7079  } else {
7080  V[3] >>= 1;
7081  V[3] |= ((V[2] & 0x00000001) ? 0x80000000 : 0);
7082  V[2] >>= 1;
7083  V[2] |= ((V[1] & 0x00000001) ? 0x80000000 : 0);
7084  V[1] >>= 1;
7085  V[1] |= ((V[0] & 0x00000001) ? 0x80000000 : 0);
7086  V[0] >>= 1;
7087  }
7088  y <<= 1;
7089  }
7090  }
7091  X[0] = Z[0];
7092  X[1] = Z[1];
7093  X[2] = Z[2];
7094  X[3] = Z[3];
7095 }
7096 
7097 
7098 void GHASH(Aes* aes, const byte* a, word32 aSz, const byte* c,
7099  word32 cSz, byte* s, word32 sSz)
7100 {
7101  word32 x[4] = {0,0,0,0};
7102  word32 blocks, partial;
7103  word32 bigH[4];
7104 
7105  XMEMCPY(bigH, aes->H, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7106  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7107  ByteReverseWords(bigH, bigH, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7108  #endif
7109 
7110  /* Hash in A, the Additional Authentication Data */
7111  if (aSz != 0 && a != NULL) {
7112  word32 bigA[4];
7113  blocks = aSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7114  partial = aSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7115  while (blocks--) {
7116  XMEMCPY(bigA, a, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7117  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7118  ByteReverseWords(bigA, bigA, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7119  #endif
7120  x[0] ^= bigA[0];
7121  x[1] ^= bigA[1];
7122  x[2] ^= bigA[2];
7123  x[3] ^= bigA[3];
7124  GMULT(x, bigH);
7125  a += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7126  }
7127  if (partial != 0) {
7128  XMEMSET(bigA, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7129  XMEMCPY(bigA, a, partial);
7130  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7131  ByteReverseWords(bigA, bigA, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7132  #endif
7133  x[0] ^= bigA[0];
7134  x[1] ^= bigA[1];
7135  x[2] ^= bigA[2];
7136  x[3] ^= bigA[3];
7137  GMULT(x, bigH);
7138  }
7139  }
7140 
7141  /* Hash in C, the Ciphertext */
7142  if (cSz != 0 && c != NULL) {
7143  word32 bigC[4];
7144  blocks = cSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7145  partial = cSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7146  while (blocks--) {
7147  XMEMCPY(bigC, c, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7148  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7149  ByteReverseWords(bigC, bigC, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7150  #endif
7151  x[0] ^= bigC[0];
7152  x[1] ^= bigC[1];
7153  x[2] ^= bigC[2];
7154  x[3] ^= bigC[3];
7155  GMULT(x, bigH);
7156  c += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7157  }
7158  if (partial != 0) {
7159  XMEMSET(bigC, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7160  XMEMCPY(bigC, c, partial);
7161  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7162  ByteReverseWords(bigC, bigC, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7163  #endif
7164  x[0] ^= bigC[0];
7165  x[1] ^= bigC[1];
7166  x[2] ^= bigC[2];
7167  x[3] ^= bigC[3];
7168  GMULT(x, bigH);
7169  }
7170  }
7171 
7172  /* Hash in the lengths in bits of A and C */
7173  {
7174  word32 len[4];
7175 
7176  /* Lengths are in bytes. Convert to bits. */
7177  len[0] = (aSz >> (8*sizeof(aSz) - 3));
7178  len[1] = aSz << 3;
7179  len[2] = (cSz >> (8*sizeof(cSz) - 3));
7180  len[3] = cSz << 3;
7181 
7182  x[0] ^= len[0];
7183  x[1] ^= len[1];
7184  x[2] ^= len[2];
7185  x[3] ^= len[3];
7186  GMULT(x, bigH);
7187  }
7188  #ifdef LITTLE_ENDIAN_ORDER
7189  ByteReverseWords(x, x, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7190  #endif
7191  XMEMCPY(s, x, sSz);
7192 }
7193 
7194 #endif /* end GCM_WORD32 */
7195 
7196 
7197 #if !defined(WOLFSSL_XILINX_CRYPT)
7198 int wc_AesGcmEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz,
7199  const byte* iv, word32 ivSz,
7200  byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
7201  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
7202 {
7203  int ret = 0;
7204  word32 keySize;
7205 #ifdef FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM
7206  status_t status;
7207 #else
7208  word32 blocks = sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7209  word32 partial = sz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7210  const byte* p = in;
7211  byte* c = out;
7212  byte counter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7213  byte initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7214  byte *ctr;
7215  byte scratch[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7216 #if defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
7217  #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
7218  CRYP_HandleTypeDef hcryp;
7219  #else
7220  byte keyCopy[AES_BLOCK_SIZE * 2];
7221  #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
7222  int status = 0;
7223  byte* authInPadded = NULL;
7224  byte tag[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7225  int authPadSz;
7226 #endif /* STM32F2_CRYPTO || STM32F4_CRYPTO */
7227 #endif /* FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM */
7228 
7229  /* argument checks */
7230  if (aes == NULL || authTagSz > AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
7231  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7232  }
7233 
7234  if (authTagSz < WOLFSSL_MIN_AUTH_TAG_SZ) {
7235  WOLFSSL_MSG("GcmEncrypt authTagSz too small error");
7236  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7237  }
7238 
7239  ret = wc_AesGetKeySize(aes, &keySize);
7240  if (ret != 0)
7241  return ret;
7242 
7243 #ifdef FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM
7244 
7245  status = LTC_AES_EncryptTagGcm(LTC_BASE, in, out, sz, iv, ivSz,
7246  authIn, authInSz, (byte*)aes->key, keySize, authTag, authTagSz);
7247 
7248  ret = (status == kStatus_Success) ? 0 : AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7249 
7250 #else
7251 
7252 #if defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
7253 
7254  /* additional argument checks - STM32 HW only supports 12 byte IV */
7255  if (ivSz != NONCE_SZ) {
7256  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7257  }
7258 
7259  XMEMSET(initialCounter, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7260  XMEMCPY(initialCounter, iv, ivSz);
7261  initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1] = STM32_GCM_IV_START;
7262 
7263  /* STM32 HW AES-GCM requires / assumes inputs are a multiple of block size.
7264  * We can avoid this by zero padding (authIn) AAD, but zero-padded plaintext
7265  * will be encrypted and output incorrectly, causing a bad authTag.
7266  * We will use HW accelerated AES-GCM if plain%AES_BLOCK_SZ==0.
7267  * Otherwise, we will use accelerated AES_CTR for encrypt, and then
7268  * perform GHASH in software.
7269  * See NIST SP 800-38D */
7270 
7271  /* Plain text is a multiple of block size, so use HW-Accelerated AES_GCM */
7272  if (!partial) {
7273  /* pad authIn if it is not a block multiple */
7274  if ((authInSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE) != 0) {
7275  authPadSz = ((authInSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE) + 1) * AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7276  /* Need to pad the AAD to a full block with zeros. */
7277  authInPadded = XMALLOC(authPadSz, aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7278  if (authInPadded == NULL) {
7279  return MEMORY_E;
7280  }
7281  XMEMSET(authInPadded, 0, authPadSz);
7282  XMEMCPY(authInPadded, authIn, authInSz);
7283  } else {
7284  authPadSz = authInSz;
7285  authInPadded = (byte*)authIn;
7286  }
7287 
7288 
7289  #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
7290  XMEMSET(&hcryp, 0, sizeof(CRYP_HandleTypeDef));
7291  switch (keySize) {
7292  case 16: /* 128-bit key */
7293  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_128B;
7294  break;
7295  case 24: /* 192-bit key */
7296  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;
7297  break;
7298  case 32: /* 256-bit key */
7299  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_256B;
7300  break;
7301  default:
7302  break;
7303  }
7304  hcryp.Instance = CRYP;
7305  hcryp.Init.DataType = CRYP_DATATYPE_8B;
7306  hcryp.Init.pKey = (byte*)aes->key;
7307  hcryp.Init.pInitVect = initialCounter;
7308  hcryp.Init.Header = authInPadded;
7309  hcryp.Init.HeaderSize = authInSz;
7310 
7311  HAL_CRYP_Init(&hcryp);
7312  status = HAL_CRYPEx_AESGCM_Encrypt(&hcryp, (byte*)in, sz,
7313  out, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT);
7314  /* Compute the authTag */
7315  if (status == HAL_OK)
7316  status = HAL_CRYPEx_AESGCM_Finish(&hcryp, sz, tag, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT);
7317 
7318  if (status != HAL_OK)
7319  ret = AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7320  HAL_CRYP_DeInit(&hcryp);
7321  #else
7322  ByteReverseWords((word32*)keyCopy, (word32*)aes->key, keySize);
7323  status = CRYP_AES_GCM(MODE_ENCRYPT, (uint8_t*)initialCounter,
7324  (uint8_t*)keyCopy, keySize * 8,
7325  (uint8_t*)in, sz,
7326  (uint8_t*)authInPadded,authInSz,
7327  (uint8_t*)out, tag);
7328  if (status != SUCCESS)
7329  ret = AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7330  #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
7331 
7332  /* authTag may be shorter than AES_BLOCK_SZ, store separately */
7333  if (ret == 0)
7334  XMEMCPY(authTag, tag, authTagSz);
7335 
7336  /* We only allocate extra memory if authInPadded is not a multiple of AES_BLOCK_SZ */
7337  if (authInPadded != NULL && authInSz != authPadSz) {
7338  XFREE(authInPadded, aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7339  }
7340 
7341  return ret;
7342  }
7343 
7344 #endif
7345 
7346  /* Software AES-GCM */
7347 
7348 #if defined(WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT) && defined(WC_ASYNC_ENABLE_AES)
7349  /* if async and byte count above threshold */
7350  if (aes->asyncDev.marker == WOLFSSL_ASYNC_MARKER_AES &&
7351  sz >= WC_ASYNC_THRESH_AES_GCM) {
7352  #if defined(HAVE_CAVIUM)
7353  /* Not yet supported, contact wolfSSL if interested in using */
7354  #elif defined(HAVE_INTEL_QA)
7355  return IntelQaSymAesGcmEncrypt(&aes->asyncDev, out, in, sz,
7356  (const byte*)aes->asyncKey, aes->keylen, iv, ivSz,
7357  authTag, authTagSz, authIn, authInSz);
7358  #else /* WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT_TEST */
7359  if (wc_AsyncTestInit(&aes->asyncDev, ASYNC_TEST_AES_GCM_ENCRYPT)) {
7360  WC_ASYNC_TEST* testDev = &aes->asyncDev.test;
7361  testDev->aes.aes = aes;
7362  testDev->aes.out = out;
7363  testDev->aes.in = in;
7364  testDev->aes.sz = sz;
7365  testDev->aes.iv = iv;
7366  testDev->aes.ivSz = ivSz;
7367  testDev->aes.authTag = authTag;
7368  testDev->aes.authTagSz = authTagSz;
7369  testDev->aes.authIn = authIn;
7370  testDev->aes.authInSz = authInSz;
7371  return WC_PENDING_E;
7372  }
7373  #endif
7374  }
7375 #endif /* WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT */
7376 
7377 #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
7378  if (haveAESNI) {
7379  #ifdef HAVE_INTEL_AVX2
7380  if (IS_INTEL_AVX2(intel_flags)) {
7381  AES_GCM_encrypt_avx2(in, out, authIn, iv, authTag,
7382  sz, authInSz, ivSz, (const byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds);
7383  }
7384  else
7385  #endif
7386  AES_GCM_encrypt(in, out, authIn, iv, authTag,
7387  sz, authInSz, ivSz, (const byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds);
7388  return 0;
7389  }
7390 #endif
7391 
7392  ctr = counter;
7393  XMEMSET(initialCounter, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7394  if (ivSz == NONCE_SZ) {
7395  XMEMCPY(initialCounter, iv, ivSz);
7396  initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1] = 1;
7397  }
7398  else {
7399  GHASH(aes, NULL, 0, iv, ivSz, initialCounter, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7400  }
7401  XMEMCPY(ctr, initialCounter, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7402 
7403 #ifdef WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT
7404  if (blocks) {
7405  /* use intitial IV for PIC32 HW, but don't use it below */
7406  XMEMCPY(aes->iv_ce, ctr, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7407 
7408  ret = wc_Pic32AesCrypt(
7409  aes->key_ce, aes->keylen, aes->iv_ce, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
7410  out, in, (blocks * AES_BLOCK_SIZE),
7411  PIC32_ENCRYPTION, PIC32_ALGO_AES, PIC32_CRYPTOALGO_AES_GCM);
7412  if (ret != 0)
7413  return ret;
7414  }
7415  /* process remainder using partial handling */
7416 #endif
7417  while (blocks--) {
7418  IncrementGcmCounter(ctr);
7419  #ifndef WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT
7420  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, ctr, scratch);
7421  xorbuf(scratch, p, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7422  XMEMCPY(c, scratch, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7423  #endif
7424  p += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7425  c += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7426  }
7427 
7428  if (partial != 0) {
7429  IncrementGcmCounter(ctr);
7430  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, ctr, scratch);
7431  xorbuf(scratch, p, partial);
7432  XMEMCPY(c, scratch, partial);
7433 
7434  }
7435 
7436  GHASH(aes, authIn, authInSz, out, sz, authTag, authTagSz);
7437  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, initialCounter, scratch);
7438  xorbuf(authTag, scratch, authTagSz);
7439 
7440 #endif /* FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM */
7441 
7442  return ret;
7443 }
7444 
7445 
7446 #if defined(HAVE_AES_DECRYPT) || defined(HAVE_AESGCM_DECRYPT)
7447 int wc_AesGcmDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 sz,
7448  const byte* iv, word32 ivSz,
7449  const byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
7450  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
7451 {
7452  int ret = 0;
7453  word32 keySize;
7454 #ifdef FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM
7455  status_t status;
7456 #elif defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
7457  #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
7458  CRYP_HandleTypeDef hcryp;
7459  #else
7460  byte keyCopy[AES_BLOCK_SIZE * 2];
7461  #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
7462  int status;
7463  int inPadSz, authPadSz;
7464  byte tag[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7465  byte *inPadded = NULL;
7466  byte *authInPadded = NULL;
7467  byte initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7468 #else /* software AES-GCM */
7469  word32 blocks = sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7470  word32 partial = sz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7471  const byte* c = in;
7472  byte* p = out;
7473  byte counter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7474  byte initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7475  byte *ctr;
7476  byte scratch[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7477  byte Tprime[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7478  byte EKY0[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7479 #endif
7480 
7481  /* argument checks */
7482  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL || iv == NULL ||
7483  authTag == NULL || authTagSz > AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
7484  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7485  }
7486 
7487  ret = wc_AesGetKeySize(aes, &keySize);
7488  if (ret != 0) {
7489  return ret;
7490  }
7491 
7492 #ifdef FREESCALE_LTC_AES_GCM
7493 
7494  status = LTC_AES_DecryptTagGcm(LTC_BASE, in, out, sz, iv, ivSz,
7495  authIn, authInSz, (byte*)aes->key, keySize, authTag, authTagSz);
7496 
7497  ret = (status == kStatus_Success) ? 0 : AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7498 
7499 #elif defined(STM32F2_CRYPTO) || defined(STM32F4_CRYPTO)
7500 
7501  /* additional argument checks - STM32 HW only supports 12 byte IV */
7502  if (ivSz != NONCE_SZ) {
7503  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7504  }
7505 
7506  XMEMSET(initialCounter, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7507  XMEMCPY(initialCounter, iv, ivSz);
7508  initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1] = STM32_GCM_IV_START;
7509 
7510  /* Need to pad the AAD and input cipher text to a full block size since
7511  * CRYP_AES_GCM will assume these are a multiple of AES_BLOCK_SIZE.
7512  * It is okay to pad with zeros because GCM does this before GHASH already.
7513  * See NIST SP 800-38D */
7514 
7515  if ((sz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE) > 0) {
7516  inPadSz = ((sz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE) + 1) * AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7517  inPadded = XMALLOC(inPadSz, aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7518  if (inPadded == NULL) {
7519  return MEMORY_E;
7520  }
7521  XMEMSET(inPadded, 0, inPadSz);
7522  XMEMCPY(inPadded, in, sz);
7523  } else {
7524  inPadSz = sz;
7525  inPadded = (byte*)in;
7526  }
7527 
7528  if ((authInSz % AES_BLOCK_SIZE) > 0) {
7529  authPadSz = ((authInSz / AES_BLOCK_SIZE) + 1) * AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7530  authInPadded = XMALLOC(authPadSz, aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7531  if (authInPadded == NULL) {
7532  if (inPadded != NULL && inPadSz != sz)
7533  XFREE(inPadded , aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7534  return MEMORY_E;
7535  }
7536  XMEMSET(authInPadded, 0, authPadSz);
7537  XMEMCPY(authInPadded, authIn, authInSz);
7538  } else {
7539  authPadSz = authInSz;
7540  authInPadded = (byte*)authIn;
7541  }
7542 
7543 #ifdef WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX
7544  XMEMSET(&hcryp, 0, sizeof(CRYP_HandleTypeDef));
7545  switch(keySize) {
7546  case 16: /* 128-bit key */
7547  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_128B;
7548  break;
7549  case 24: /* 192-bit key */
7550  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_192B;
7551  break;
7552  case 32: /* 256-bit key */
7553  hcryp.Init.KeySize = CRYP_KEYSIZE_256B;
7554  break;
7555  default:
7556  break;
7557  }
7558  hcryp.Instance = CRYP;
7559  hcryp.Init.DataType = CRYP_DATATYPE_8B;
7560  hcryp.Init.pKey = (byte*)aes->key;
7561  hcryp.Init.pInitVect = initialCounter;
7562  hcryp.Init.Header = authInPadded;
7563  hcryp.Init.HeaderSize = authInSz;
7564 
7565  HAL_CRYP_Init(&hcryp);
7566  /* Use inPadded for output buffer instead of
7567  * out so that we don't overflow our size. */
7568  status = HAL_CRYPEx_AESGCM_Decrypt(&hcryp, (byte*)inPadded,
7569  sz, inPadded, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT);
7570  /* Compute the authTag */
7571  if (status == HAL_OK)
7572  status = HAL_CRYPEx_AESGCM_Finish(&hcryp, sz, tag, STM32_HAL_TIMEOUT);
7573 
7574  if (status != HAL_OK)
7575  ret = AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7576 
7577  HAL_CRYP_DeInit(&hcryp);
7578 #else
7579  ByteReverseWords((word32*)keyCopy, (word32*)aes->key, keySize);
7580 
7581  /* Input size and auth size need to be the actual sizes, even though
7582  * they are not block aligned, because this length (in bits) is used
7583  * in the final GHASH. Use inPadded for output buffer instead of
7584  * out so that we don't overflow our size. */
7585  status = CRYP_AES_GCM(MODE_DECRYPT, (uint8_t*)initialCounter,
7586  (uint8_t*)keyCopy, keySize * 8,
7587  (uint8_t*)inPadded, sz,
7588  (uint8_t*)authInPadded,authInSz,
7589  (uint8_t*)inPadded, tag);
7590  if (status != SUCCESS)
7591  ret = AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7592 #endif /* WOLFSSL_STM32_CUBEMX */
7593 
7594  if (ret == 0 && ConstantCompare(authTag, tag, authTagSz) == 0) {
7595  /* Only keep the decrypted data if authTag success. */
7596  XMEMCPY(out, inPadded, sz);
7597  ret = 0; /* success */
7598  }
7599 
7600  /* only allocate padding buffers if the inputs are not a multiple of block sz */
7601  if (inPadded != NULL && inPadSz != sz)
7602  XFREE(inPadded , aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7603  if (authInPadded != NULL && authPadSz != authInSz)
7604  XFREE(authInPadded, aes->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7605 
7606 #else
7607 
7608  /* software AES GCM */
7609 
7610 #if defined(WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT) && defined(WC_ASYNC_ENABLE_AES)
7611  /* if async and byte count above threshold */
7612  if (aes->asyncDev.marker == WOLFSSL_ASYNC_MARKER_AES &&
7613  sz >= WC_ASYNC_THRESH_AES_GCM) {
7614  #if defined(HAVE_CAVIUM)
7615  /* Not yet supported, contact wolfSSL if interested in using */
7616  #elif defined(HAVE_INTEL_QA)
7617  return IntelQaSymAesGcmDecrypt(&aes->asyncDev, out, in, sz,
7618  (const byte*)aes->asyncKey, aes->keylen, iv, ivSz,
7619  authTag, authTagSz, authIn, authInSz);
7620  #else /* WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT_TEST */
7621  if (wc_AsyncTestInit(&aes->asyncDev, ASYNC_TEST_AES_GCM_DECRYPT)) {
7622  WC_ASYNC_TEST* testDev = &aes->asyncDev.test;
7623  testDev->aes.aes = aes;
7624  testDev->aes.out = out;
7625  testDev->aes.in = in;
7626  testDev->aes.sz = sz;
7627  testDev->aes.iv = iv;
7628  testDev->aes.ivSz = ivSz;
7629  testDev->aes.authTag = (byte*)authTag;
7630  testDev->aes.authTagSz = authTagSz;
7631  testDev->aes.authIn = authIn;
7632  testDev->aes.authInSz = authInSz;
7633  return WC_PENDING_E;
7634  }
7635  #endif
7636  }
7637 #endif /* WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT */
7638 
7639 #ifdef WOLFSSL_AESNI
7640  if (haveAESNI) {
7641  #ifdef HAVE_INTEL_AVX2
7642  if (IS_INTEL_AVX2(intel_flags)) {
7643  if (AES_GCM_decrypt_avx2(in, out, authIn, iv, authTag, sz, authInSz,
7644  ivSz, (byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds) == 0)
7645  return AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7646  }
7647  else
7648  #endif
7649  if (AES_GCM_decrypt(in, out, authIn, iv, authTag, sz, authInSz, ivSz,
7650  (byte*)aes->key, aes->rounds) == 0)
7651  return AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7652  return 0;
7653  }
7654 #endif
7655 
7656  ctr = counter;
7657  XMEMSET(initialCounter, 0, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7658  if (ivSz == NONCE_SZ) {
7659  XMEMCPY(initialCounter, iv, ivSz);
7660  initialCounter[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1] = 1;
7661  }
7662  else {
7663  GHASH(aes, NULL, 0, iv, ivSz, initialCounter, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7664  }
7665  XMEMCPY(ctr, initialCounter, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7666 
7667  /* Calc the authTag again using the received auth data and the cipher text */
7668  GHASH(aes, authIn, authInSz, in, sz, Tprime, sizeof(Tprime));
7669  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, ctr, EKY0);
7670  xorbuf(Tprime, EKY0, sizeof(Tprime));
7671 
7672  if (ConstantCompare(authTag, Tprime, authTagSz) != 0) {
7673  return AES_GCM_AUTH_E;
7674  }
7675 
7676 #ifdef WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT
7677  if (blocks) {
7678  /* use intitial IV for PIC32 HW, but don't use it below */
7679  XMEMCPY(aes->iv_ce, ctr, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7680 
7681  ret = wc_Pic32AesCrypt(
7682  aes->key_ce, aes->keylen, aes->iv_ce, AES_BLOCK_SIZE,
7683  out, in, (blocks * AES_BLOCK_SIZE),
7684  PIC32_DECRYPTION, PIC32_ALGO_AES, PIC32_CRYPTOALGO_AES_GCM);
7685  if (ret != 0)
7686  return ret;
7687  }
7688  /* process remainder using partial handling */
7689 #endif
7690 
7691  while (blocks--) {
7692  IncrementGcmCounter(ctr);
7693  #ifndef WOLFSSL_PIC32MZ_CRYPT
7694  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, ctr, scratch);
7695  xorbuf(scratch, c, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7696  XMEMCPY(p, scratch, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7697  #endif
7698  p += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7699  c += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7700  }
7701  if (partial != 0) {
7702  IncrementGcmCounter(ctr);
7703  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, ctr, scratch);
7704  xorbuf(scratch, c, partial);
7705  XMEMCPY(p, scratch, partial);
7706  }
7707 
7708 #endif
7709 
7710  return ret;
7711 }
7712 
7713 #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT || HAVE_AESGCM_DECRYPT */
7714 #endif /* (WOLFSSL_XILINX_CRYPT) */
7715

7748 /* return 0 on success */
7749 int wc_AesCcmEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
7750  const byte* nonce, word32 nonceSz,
7751  byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
7752  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)

7757

7767  return status;
7768  }

7776 #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
7777 int wc_AesCcmDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
7778  const byte* nonce, word32 nonceSz,
7779  const byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
7780  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
7781 {
7782  byte *key;
7783  uint32_t keySize;
7784  status_t status;
7785 
7786  /* sanity check on arguments */
7787  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL || nonce == NULL
7788  || authTag == NULL || nonceSz < 7 || nonceSz > 13)
7789  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;

7800

7802  return 0;

7812 /* software AES CCM */
7813 #else
7814 
7815 static void roll_x(Aes* aes, const byte* in, word32 inSz, byte* out)
7816 {
7817  /* process the bulk of the data */
7818  while (inSz >= AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
7819  xorbuf(out, in, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7820  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7821  inSz -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7822 
7823  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, out, out);
7824  }
7825 
7826  /* process remainder of the data */
7827  if (inSz > 0) {
7828  xorbuf(out, in, inSz);
7829  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, out, out);
7830  }
7831 }
7832 
7833 static void roll_auth(Aes* aes, const byte* in, word32 inSz, byte* out)
7834 {
7835  word32 authLenSz;
7836  word32 remainder;
7837 
7838  /* encode the length in */
7839  if (inSz <= 0xFEFF) {
7840  authLenSz = 2;
7841  out[0] ^= ((inSz & 0xFF00) >> 8);
7842  out[1] ^= (inSz & 0x00FF);
7843  }
7844  else if (inSz <= 0xFFFFFFFF) {
7845  authLenSz = 6;
7846  out[0] ^= 0xFF; out[1] ^= 0xFE;
7847  out[2] ^= ((inSz & 0xFF000000) >> 24);
7848  out[3] ^= ((inSz & 0x00FF0000) >> 16);
7849  out[4] ^= ((inSz & 0x0000FF00) >> 8);
7850  out[5] ^= (inSz & 0x000000FF);
7851  }
7852  /* Note, the protocol handles auth data up to 2^64, but we are
7853  * using 32-bit sizes right now, so the bigger data isn't handled
7854  * else if (inSz <= 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF) {} */
7855  else
7856  return;
7857 
7858  /* start fill out the rest of the first block */
7859  remainder = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - authLenSz;
7860  if (inSz >= remainder) {
7861  /* plenty of bulk data to fill the remainder of this block */
7862  xorbuf(out + authLenSz, in, remainder);
7863  inSz -= remainder;
7864  in += remainder;
7865  }
7866  else {
7867  /* not enough bulk data, copy what is available, and pad zero */
7868  xorbuf(out + authLenSz, in, inSz);
7869  inSz = 0;
7870  }
7871  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, out, out);
7872 
7873  if (inSz > 0)
7874  roll_x(aes, in, inSz, out);
7875 }
7876 
7877 
7878 static INLINE void AesCcmCtrInc(byte* B, word32 lenSz)
7879 {
7880  word32 i;
7881 
7882  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++) {
7883  if (++B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] != 0) return;
7884  }
7885 }
7886 
7887 /* return 0 on success */
7888 int wc_AesCcmEncrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
7889  const byte* nonce, word32 nonceSz,
7890  byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
7891  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
7892 {
7893  byte A[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7894  byte B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7895  byte lenSz;
7896  word32 i;
7897  byte mask = 0xFF;
7898  const word32 wordSz = (word32)sizeof(word32);
7899 
7900  /* sanity check on arguments */
7901  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL || nonce == NULL
7902  || authTag == NULL || nonceSz < 7 || nonceSz > 13)
7903  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7904 
7905  XMEMCPY(B+1, nonce, nonceSz);
7906  lenSz = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - (byte)nonceSz;
7907  B[0] = (authInSz > 0 ? 64 : 0)
7908  + (8 * (((byte)authTagSz - 2) / 2))
7909  + (lenSz - 1);
7910  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++) {
7911  if (mask && i >= wordSz)
7912  mask = 0x00;
7913  B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] = (inSz >> ((8 * i) & mask)) & mask;
7914  }
7915 
7916  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
7917 
7918  if (authInSz > 0)
7919  roll_auth(aes, authIn, authInSz, A);
7920  if (inSz > 0)
7921  roll_x(aes, in, inSz, A);
7922  XMEMCPY(authTag, A, authTagSz);
7923 
7924  B[0] = lenSz - 1;
7925  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++)
7926  B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] = 0;
7927  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
7928  xorbuf(authTag, A, authTagSz);
7929 
7930  B[15] = 1;
7931  while (inSz >= AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
7932  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
7933  xorbuf(A, in, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7934  XMEMCPY(out, A, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7935 
7936  AesCcmCtrInc(B, lenSz);
7937  inSz -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7938  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7939  out += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7940  }
7941  if (inSz > 0) {
7942  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
7943  xorbuf(A, in, inSz);
7944  XMEMCPY(out, A, inSz);
7945  }
7946 
7947  ForceZero(A, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7948  ForceZero(B, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7949 
7950  return 0;
7951 }
7952 
7953 #ifdef HAVE_AES_DECRYPT
7954 int wc_AesCcmDecrypt(Aes* aes, byte* out, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
7955  const byte* nonce, word32 nonceSz,
7956  const byte* authTag, word32 authTagSz,
7957  const byte* authIn, word32 authInSz)
7958 {
7959  byte A[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7960  byte B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
7961  byte* o;
7962  byte lenSz;
7963  word32 i, oSz;
7964  int result = 0;
7965  byte mask = 0xFF;
7966  const word32 wordSz = (word32)sizeof(word32);
7967 
7968  /* sanity check on arguments */
7969  if (aes == NULL || out == NULL || in == NULL || nonce == NULL
7970  || authTag == NULL || nonceSz < 7 || nonceSz > 13)
7971  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7972 
7973  o = out;
7974  oSz = inSz;
7975  XMEMCPY(B+1, nonce, nonceSz);
7976  lenSz = AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - (byte)nonceSz;
7977 
7978  B[0] = lenSz - 1;
7979  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++)
7980  B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] = 0;
7981  B[15] = 1;
7982 
7983  while (oSz >= AES_BLOCK_SIZE) {
7984  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
7985  xorbuf(A, in, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7986  XMEMCPY(o, A, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
7987 
7988  AesCcmCtrInc(B, lenSz);
7989  oSz -= AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7990  in += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7991  o += AES_BLOCK_SIZE;
7992  }
7993  if (inSz > 0) {
7994  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
7995  xorbuf(A, in, oSz);
7996  XMEMCPY(o, A, oSz);
7997  }
7998 
7999  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++)
8000  B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] = 0;
8001  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
8002 
8003  o = out;
8004  oSz = inSz;
8005 
8006  B[0] = (authInSz > 0 ? 64 : 0)
8007  + (8 * (((byte)authTagSz - 2) / 2))
8008  + (lenSz - 1);
8009  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++) {
8010  if (mask && i >= wordSz)
8011  mask = 0x00;
8012  B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] = (inSz >> ((8 * i) & mask)) & mask;
8013  }
8014 
8015  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, A);
8016 
8017  if (authInSz > 0)
8018  roll_auth(aes, authIn, authInSz, A);
8019  if (inSz > 0)
8020  roll_x(aes, o, oSz, A);
8021 
8022  B[0] = lenSz - 1;
8023  for (i = 0; i < lenSz; i++)
8024  B[AES_BLOCK_SIZE - 1 - i] = 0;
8025  wc_AesEncrypt(aes, B, B);
8026  xorbuf(A, B, authTagSz);
8027 
8028  if (ConstantCompare(A, authTag, authTagSz) != 0) {
8029  /* If the authTag check fails, don't keep the decrypted data.
8030  * Unfortunately, you need the decrypted data to calculate the
8031  * check value. */
8032  XMEMSET(out, 0, inSz);
8033  result = AES_CCM_AUTH_E;
8034  }
8035 
8036  ForceZero(A, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
8037  ForceZero(B, AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
8038  o = NULL;
8039 
8040  return result;
8041 }
8042 #endif /* HAVE_AES_DECRYPT */
8043 #endif /* software AES CCM */
8044 
8045 #endif /* HAVE_AESCCM */

8080 int wc_AesGetKeySize(Aes* aes, word32* keySize)
8081 {
8082  int ret = 0;
8083 
8084  if (aes == NULL || keySize == NULL) {
8085  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8086  }
8087 
8088  switch (aes->rounds) {
8089  case 10:
8090  *keySize = 16;
8091  break;
8092  case 12:
8093  *keySize = 24;
8094  break;
8095  case 14:
8096  *keySize = 32;
8097  break;
8098  default:
8099  *keySize = 0;
8100  ret = BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8101  }
8102 
8103  return ret;
8104 }

8109 
8110 #ifdef HAVE_AES_KEYWRAP
8111 
8112 /* Initialize key wrap counter with value */
8113 static INLINE void InitKeyWrapCounter(byte* inOutCtr, word32 value)
8114 {
8115  int i;
8116  word32 bytes;
8117 
8118  bytes = sizeof(word32);
8119  for (i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(word32); i++) {
8120  inOutCtr[i+sizeof(word32)] = (value >> ((bytes - 1) * 8)) & 0xFF;
8121  bytes--;
8122  }
8123 }
8124 
8125 /* Increment key wrap counter */
8126 static INLINE void IncrementKeyWrapCounter(byte* inOutCtr)
8127 {
8128  int i;
8129 
8130  /* in network byte order so start at end and work back */
8131  for (i = KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
8132  if (++inOutCtr[i]) /* we're done unless we overflow */
8133  return;
8134  }
8135 }
8136 
8137 /* Decrement key wrap counter */
8138 static INLINE void DecrementKeyWrapCounter(byte* inOutCtr)
8139 {
8140  int i;
8141 
8142  for (i = KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
8143  if (--inOutCtr[i] != 0xFF) /* we're done unless we underflow */
8144  return;
8145  }
8146 }
8147 
8148 /* perform AES key wrap (RFC3394), return out sz on success, negative on err */
8149 int wc_AesKeyWrap(const byte* key, word32 keySz, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
8150  byte* out, word32 outSz, const byte* iv)
8151 {
8152  Aes aes;
8153  byte* r;
8154  word32 i;
8155  int ret, j;
8156 
8157  byte t[KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE];
8158  byte tmp[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
8159 
8160  /* n must be at least 2, output size is n + 8 bytes */
8161  if (key == NULL || in == NULL || inSz < 2 ||
8162  out == NULL || outSz < (inSz + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE))
8163  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8164 
8165  /* input must be multiple of 64-bits */
8166  if (inSz % KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE != 0)
8167  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8168 
8169  /* user IV is optional */
8170  if (iv == NULL) {
8171  XMEMSET(tmp, 0xA6, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8172  } else {
8173  XMEMCPY(tmp, iv, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8174  }
8175 
8176  r = out + 8;
8177  XMEMCPY(r, in, inSz);
8178  XMEMSET(t, 0, sizeof(t));
8179 
8180  ret = wc_AesInit(&aes, NULL, INVALID_DEVID);
8181  if (ret != 0)
8182  return ret;
8183 
8184  ret = wc_AesSetKey(&aes, key, keySz, NULL, AES_ENCRYPTION);
8185  if (ret != 0)
8186  return ret;
8187 
8188  for (j = 0; j <= 5; j++) {
8189  for (i = 1; i <= inSz / KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE; i++) {
8190 
8191  /* load R[i] */
8192  XMEMCPY(tmp + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE, r, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8193 
8194  wc_AesEncryptDirect(&aes, tmp, tmp);
8195 
8196  /* calculate new A */
8197  IncrementKeyWrapCounter(t);
8198  xorbuf(tmp, t, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8199 
8200  /* save R[i] */
8201  XMEMCPY(r, tmp + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8202  r += KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE;
8203  }
8204  r = out + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE;
8205  }
8206 
8207  /* C[0] = A */
8208  XMEMCPY(out, tmp, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8209 
8210  wc_AesFree(&aes);
8211 
8212  return inSz + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE;
8213 }
8214 
8215 int wc_AesKeyUnWrap(const byte* key, word32 keySz, const byte* in, word32 inSz,
8216  byte* out, word32 outSz, const byte* iv)
8217 {
8218  Aes aes;
8219  byte* r;
8220  word32 i, n;
8221  int ret, j;
8222 
8223  byte t[KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE];
8224  byte tmp[AES_BLOCK_SIZE];
8225 
8226  const byte* expIv;
8227  const byte defaultIV[] = {
8228  0xA6, 0xA6, 0xA6, 0xA6, 0xA6, 0xA6, 0xA6, 0xA6
8229  };
8230 
8231  (void)iv;
8232 
8233  if (key == NULL || in == NULL || inSz < 3 ||
8234  out == NULL || outSz < (inSz - KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE))
8235  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8236 
8237  /* input must be multiple of 64-bits */
8238  if (inSz % KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE != 0)
8239  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8240 
8241  /* user IV optional */
8242  if (iv != NULL) {
8243  expIv = iv;
8244  } else {
8245  expIv = defaultIV;
8246  }
8247 
8248  /* A = C[0], R[i] = C[i] */
8249  XMEMCPY(tmp, in, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8250  XMEMCPY(out, in + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE, inSz - KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8251  XMEMSET(t, 0, sizeof(t));
8252 
8253  ret = wc_AesInit(&aes, NULL, INVALID_DEVID);
8254  if (ret != 0)
8255  return ret;
8256 
8257  ret = wc_AesSetKey(&aes, key, keySz, NULL, AES_DECRYPTION);
8258  if (ret != 0)
8259  return ret;
8260 
8261  /* initialize counter to 6n */
8262  n = (inSz - 1) / KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE;
8263  InitKeyWrapCounter(t, 6 * n);
8264 
8265  for (j = 5; j >= 0; j--) {
8266  for (i = n; i >= 1; i--) {
8267 
8268  /* calculate A */
8269  xorbuf(tmp, t, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8270  DecrementKeyWrapCounter(t);
8271 
8272  /* load R[i], starting at end of R */
8273  r = out + ((i - 1) * KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8274  XMEMCPY(tmp + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE, r, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8275  wc_AesDecryptDirect(&aes, tmp, tmp);
8276 
8277  /* save R[i] */
8278  XMEMCPY(r, tmp + KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE);
8279  }
8280  }
8281 
8282  wc_AesFree(&aes);
8283 
8284  /* verify IV */
8285  if (XMEMCMP(tmp, expIv, KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE) != 0)
8286  return BAD_KEYWRAP_IV_E;
8287 
8288  return inSz - KEYWRAP_BLOCK_SIZE;
8289 }
8290 
8291 #endif /* HAVE_AES_KEYWRAP */
8292 
8293 #endif /* HAVE_FIPS */
8294 #endif /* !NO_AES */
